        SO_YOU_WENT_AND_BECAME_A_CRAFTSMAN_AT                                   = 7087,  -- So you went and became a craftsman at another guild... And this after I told you that it was not a wise idea. What were you thinking?
        LIKE_I_TOLD_YOU_BEFORE_BECOMING_A_CRAFTSMAN                             = 7088,  -- Like I told you before, becoming a craftsman in any guild requires a high level of skill and concentration. But there is only so much that people like us can fit into our heads.
        AND_THAT_IS_WHY_I_AM_GOING_TO                                           = 7089,  -- And that is why I am going to give you a choice: revoke your craftsman status at all other guilds, or forget about your dreams of being a master woodworker.
        REVOKE_ALL_OTHER_CRAFTSMAN_STATUSES_I_M_READY                           = 7090,  -- Revoke all other craftsman statuses? I'm ready. Not on your life.
        I_KNEW_YOU_WOULD_MAKE_THE_RIGHT_DECISION                                = 7091,  -- I knew you would make the right decision. Oh, and do not worry about informing the other guildmasters. I will send a notice of your intentions right away.
        AND_I_THOUGHT_YOU_WERE_DIFFERENT_FROM_THOSE                             = 7092,  -- And I thought you were different from those other adventurers... I guess I will have to find someone else to eventually take my position as guildmaster...
        THE_SYNTHESIS_ITEMS_FOR_THAT_RANK_ARE_STILL                             = 7093,  -- The synthesis items for that rank are still beyond your skill, I'm afraid.
        IS_A_WONDERFUL_NEW_METHOD_OF_WOODWORKING_THAT_3                         = 7094,  -- % is a wonderful new method of woodworking that allows you to bundle lumber together, making it easier to process more bolts with one crystal.
        IF_YOU_THINK_THAT_AS_YOU_VE_LEARNED                                     = 7095,  -- If you think that as [a veteran/an expert/an authority/a luminary/a master] you've learned all there is to know about carpentry, think again! There is magic that can be worked with hammer and nail that would blow your mind into sawdust. Would you know more?
        STRIVE_FOR_MORE_SIGN_ME_UP_ANOTHER_TIME                                 = 7096,  -- Strive for more? Sign me up! Another time, perhaps.
        SPOKEN_LIKE_A_TRUE_CARPENTER_FIRST_YOU_LL                               = 7097,  -- Spoken like a true carpenter! First, you'll want to speak to Andreas and--assuming he's not too busy carving one of his famed wooden pheasants--obtain from him a copy of %.
        MIND_YOU_YOU_LL_HAVE_TO_HAMMER_YOURSELF                                 = 7098,  -- Mind you, you'll have to hammer yourself out a few guild points if you don't have some in stock already.
        AND_SO_THE_CARPENTER_S_HAMMER_PROVES_TOO                                = 7099,  -- And so the carpenter's hammer proves too weighty for yet another. Fear not, I shall be waiting here should you decide to heft it once more.
        HAVE_YOU_NOT_SPOKEN_WITH_ANDREAS_AS_INSTRUCTED                          = 7100,  -- Have you not spoken with Andreas as instructed? Or was he too occupied with his pheasant-carving to give you a copy of %?
        BACK_SO_SOON_HAHA_I_KNEW_THAT_DEVOURING                                 = 7101,  -- Back so soon? Haha! I knew that devouring the contents of % would be as easy for you as sawing a log.
        YOUR_NEXT_TASK_IS_TO_CRAFT_FOR_ME                                       = 7102,  -- Your next task is to craft for me %. Finding the required materials may prove a challenge in itself. You'll be needing...
        AND_DON_T_FORGET_TO_CARVE_YOUR_NAME                                     = 7103,  -- And don't forget to carve your name into your work. Think of it as applying the final coat of varnish to give your piece that special sheen!
        HAVE_YOU_BEEN_USING_THAT_HAMMER_OF_YOURS                                = 7104,  -- Have you been using that hammer of yours to beat your own head in? I just told you that making % requires...
        THIS_DOESN_T_HAPPEN_OFTEN_BUT_YOUR_PEERLESS                             = 7105,  -- ......... This doesn't happen often, %, but your peerless craftsmanship has left me at a loss for words. Let it suffice to say that you have earned the title of expert, and then some.
        WHILE_I_CANNOT_FAULT_THE_CRAFTSMANSHIP_NEITHER_CAN                      = 7106,  -- While I cannot fault the craftsmanship, neither can I credit you for a work that doesn't bear your signature.
        RULES_ARE_RULES_AND_I_CANNOT_I_WILL                                     = 7107,  -- Rules are rules, and I cannot--I will not--make exceptions even for one of your talents.
        YOUR_SKILLS_AS_A_CARPENTER_IMPRESS_ME_AND_2                             = 7108,  -- Your skills as a carpenter impress me and the others of the guild. Build for me %.
        IF_YOU_ARE_ABLE_TO_COMPLETE_THIS_TASK_2                                 = 7109,  -- If you are able to complete this task, I will grant you the title of [artisan/adept/veteran] and you will become a true member of this guild.
        HOWEVER_WHILE_I_FIND_IT_IMPOSSIBLE_TO_THINK_2                           = 7110,  -- However, while I find it impossible to think that you would do such a thing, I warn you that there could be consequences from earning this title in more than one guild.
        BECOMING_IN_ANY_GUILD_REQUIRES_A_HIGH_LEVEL                             = 7111,  -- Becoming [an artisan/an adept/a veteran] in any guild requires a high level of skill and concentration. But there is only so much that people like us can fit into our heads. Remember that.
        MIND_YOU_BECOMING_IN_ANY_GUILD_REQUIRES_A                               = 7112,  -- Mind you, becoming [an artisan/an adept/a veteran] in any guild requires a high level of skill and concentration. You would do well to remember that there is only so much knowledge we can fit in our heads.
        SO_YOU_WENT_AND_BECAME_AT_ANOTHER_GUILD                                 = 7113,  -- So you went and became [an artisan/an adept/a veteran] at another guild... And this after I told you that it was not a wise idea. What were you thinking?
        LIKE_I_TOLD_YOU_BEFORE_ACHIEVING_SUCH_A                                 = 7114,  -- Like I told you before, achieving such a rank in any guild requires a high level of skill and concentration. But there is only so much that people like us can fit into our heads.
        AND_THAT_IS_WHY_I_AM_GOING_TO_2                                         = 7115,  -- And that is why I am going to give you a choice: revoke your [artisan/adept/veteran] status at these other guilds, or forget about your dreams of being a master woodworker.
        DO_NOT_WORRY_ABOUT_INFORMING_THE_OTHER_GUILDMASTERS                     = 7116,  -- Do not worry about informing the other guildmasters. I will send a notice of your intentions right away.
        NEVER_DID_I_THINK_I_WOULD_HEAR_YOU                                      = 7117,  -- Never did I think I would hear you say those words, %. You disappoint me gravely.
        AND_YET_LET_IT_NOT_BE_SAID_THAT                                         = 7118,  -- And yet, let it not be said that we carpenters hold grudges. Should you decide to return to the path of the hammer and nail, our doors will be open for you.
        THIS_IS_THE_BLACKSMITHS_GUILD_WHERE_SKILLED_WEAPON                      = 7119,  -- This is the Blacksmiths' Guild, where skilled weapon and armorsmiths gather. Without us, a proud knight is but a paper tiger. Well, what is it, then?
        AHA_A_BASTOK_SPY_ARE_YOU_MANY_SECRETS                                   = 7120,  -- Aha! A Bastok spy, are you? Many secrets we hold dear, and pigs will fly before I surrender them!
        BAH_ANOTHER_ADVENTURER_DEVOTION_TO_OUR_CRAFT_IS                         = 7121,  -- Bah, another adventurer... Devotion to our craft is in short supply of late. Here!
        I_M_SURE_YOU_KNOW_BUT_THAT_IS                                           = 7122,  -- I'm sure you know, but that is a crystal, filled with incredible energy. No, not like blood; it is more akin to a block of coal.
        YOU_CAN_SYNTHESIZE_CRYSTALS_TO_MAKE_ALL_SORTS                           = 7123,  -- You can synthesize crystals to make all sorts of things. Focus your will upon it, bring forth the heat, and transform the materials.
        BUT_NOT_ME_I_M_NOT_FOND_OF                                              = 7124,  -- But not me! I'm not fond of using them; they're costly, and the process finishes too quickly. Yes, toil is what makes things dear!
        GO_AND_ASK_THE_OTHERS_WHAT_MATERIALS_TO                                 = 7125,  -- Go and ask the others what materials to use. And, though it pains me to say it, you may learn much about smithing by visiting Bastok.
        YOU_STILL_HAVE_MUCH_TO_LEARN_EVEN_OUR                                   = 7126,  -- You still have much to learn. Even our newest apprentices are a step ahead of you.
        YOU_THINK_YOU_VE_REACHED_THE_TOP_YOUR                                   = 7127,  -- You think you've reached the top? Your head is still in the clouds, young adventurer. Even I am still climbing...
        I_BELIEVE_YOU_ARE_READY_TO_MOVE_ON                                      = 7128,  -- I believe you are ready to move on to the next rank. Craft me %.
        FINISH_A_QUALITY_PIECE_AND_I_WILL_TEACH                                 = 7129,  -- Finish a quality piece, and I will teach you more.
        HMM_WELL_NOT_BAD_I_SHALL_PROMOTE_YOU                                    = 7130,  -- Hmm... Well, not bad. I shall promote you to the rank of [amateur/recruit/initiate/novice/apprentice]. Do not rest, for the road ahead is long.
        YES_THIS_WILL_DO_I_HEREBY_AWARD_YOU                                     = 7131,  -- Yes... This will do. I hereby award you the rank of journeyman. Congratulations. We have high hopes for you.
        WHY_BLESS_MY_BELLOWS_A_WORK_OF_ART                                      = 7132,  -- Why, bless my bellows! A work of art, indeed! You shall henceforth be addressed as artisan. May you live up to that name.
        UNBELIEVABLE_THAT_A_MERE_ADVENTURER_LIKE_YOU_COULD                      = 7133,  -- Unbelievable that a mere adventurer like you could forge such fine steel. Reminds me of when I was your age...
        I_I_M_AT_A_LOSS_FOR_WORDS                                               = 7134,  -- I...I'm at a loss for words. You've more than proven yourself as a veteran of the Blacksmiths' Guild! Why, you're almost as good as I was when I was your age...almost.
