        IS_THERE_SOMETHING_YOU_WISH_TO_KNOW                                     = 7748,  -- Is there something you wish to know?
        ARRRE_YOU_TALKING_TO_ME                                                 = 7749,  -- Arrre you talking to me?
        SPEAK_UP_SOLDIER                                                        = 7750,  -- Speak up, soldier!
        WHAT_SHALL_YOU_ASK_ABOUT_THE_COMING_BALLISTA                            = 7751,  -- What shall you ask? About the coming Ballista matches. About the Ballista schedule. About Ballista Earrings. About the rules of Ballista. Nothing at the moment.
        THE_NEXT_MATCH_WILL_BE_HELD_SHORTLY_LET                                 = 7752,  -- The next match will be held shortly. Let me inform you of the details.
        LISTEN_UP_AND_I_WILL_GIVE_YOU_A                                         = 7753,  -- Listen up, and I will give you a briefing on the details!
        THE_COMING_MATCHES_I_GUESS_I_COULD_TELL                                 = 7754,  -- The coming matches? I guess I could tell you what I know.
        THERE_ARE_NO_MATCHES_SCHEDULED_AT_THIS_TIME                             = 7755,  -- There are no matches scheduled at this time. Of course, the moment there are, you shall be the first to know.
        I_REGRET_TO_INFORM_YOU_THAT_THERE_ARE                                   = 7756,  -- I regret to inform you that there are no matches scheduled in the near future! That is all!
        THE_COMING_MATCHES_I_M_SORRY_CURRENTLY_THERE                            = 7757,  -- The coming matches? I'm sorry. Currently there are no plans for any in the near future.
        AH_YES_THE_SCHEDULE_LET_ME_READ_YOU                                     = 7758,  -- Ah yes, the schedule. Let me read you the set of dates and times.
        THOSE_FAT_CATS_UP_IN_JEUNO_HAVE_FINALLY                                 = 7759,  -- Those fat cats up in Jeuno have finally finished worrrking on the fixed schedule. Let me fill you in on what has been decided.
        REMEMBER_SOLDIER_AS_LONG_AS_I_M_ALIVE                                   = 7760,  -- Remember, soldier, as long as I'm alive, the schedule I am about to tell you is set in stone! Try to find room in your puny head to fit it in!
        I_UNDERSTAND_THIS_SCHEDULE_MAY_SEEM_CONFUSING_BUT                       = 7761,  -- I understand this schedule may seem confusing, but it is really quite simple. Perhaps you should try writing the information down?
        AH_YES_I_ALMOST_FORGOT_TO_MENTION_THAT                                  = 7762,  -- Ah yes, I almost forgot to mention that once you have participated in a match, you must wait a short period until you can make your next entry. Take this into consideration when planning which matches you will attend.
        DID_YOU_GET_ALL_THAT_IN_YOUR_PEA                                        = 7763,  -- Did you get all that in your pea-sized brain, soldier!? If you can't handle a simple schedule like that one, you're too stupid to participate in Ballista! That is all!
        AND_ONCE_YOU_HAVE_TAKEN_PART_IN_A                                       = 7764,  -- And! Once you have taken part in a match, you will not be able to immediately participate again. Think about this when choosing which matches to attend! That is all!
        DID_YOU_GET_ALL_THAT_WHAT_IT_S                                          = 7765,  -- Did you get all that? What? It's too complicated? Well, you can always do what I do and wrrrite it down.
        OH_AND_ONE_MORE_THING_ONCE_YOU_VE                                       = 7766,  -- Oh, and one more thing. Once you've parrrticipated in a match, you must wait a few days before signing up again. Think about that when planning which days to attend.
        YOUR_AIR_YOUR_ATTIRE_AN_ADVENTURER_I_ASSUME                             = 7767,  -- Your air... Your attire... An adventurer, I assume. Have you come looking to register for Conflict?
        I_TRULY_AM_SORRY_BUT_WE_ARE_NOT                                         = 7768,  -- I truly am sorry, but we are not accepting applications from those who have yet to prove their loyalty to the crown.
        HOWEVER_DO_NOT_LET_THAT_DAMPEN_YOUR_SPIRITS                             = 7769,  -- However, do not let that dampen your spirits. I am positive the day will come when I can welcome you to our noble ranks.
        THE_FUTURE_OF_OUR_KINGDOM_IS_RIDING_ON                                  = 7770,  -- The future of our kingdom is riding on your shoulders.
        WAIT_A_MINUTE_DON_T_TELL_ME_YOU                                         = 7771,  -- Wait a minute, don't tell me... You'rrre one of the Federation's adventurers, right? And you want to sign up for Conflict?
        HMMM_I_DON_T_KNOW_YOUR_RANK_IS                                          = 7772,  -- Hmmm... I don't know... Your rank is awfully low. How am I supposed to trrrust someone who hasn't prrroved themselves to the nation?
        GET_OUT_THERE_AND_DO_SOME_MISSIONS_AND                                  = 7773,  -- Get out there and do some missions, and I'll guarantee you a spot on our team. You look like you've got what it takes!
        WHAT_YOU_THINK_YOU_RE_MAN_WOMAN_ENOUGH                                  = 7774,  -- What!? You think you're man/woman] enough to join our nation's Conflict forces!?
        WHY_YOU_RE_STILL_A_WORTHLESS_MAGGOT_THAT                                = 7775,  -- Why, you're still a worthless maggot that hasn't done squat for the Republic! Come back when your rank is at least higher than your IQ!
        I_LL_BE_WATCHING_YOU_SOLDIER                                            = 7776,  -- I'll be watching you, soldier!
        YOUR_AIR_YOUR_ATTIRE_AN_ADVENTURER_I_ASSUME_2                           = 7777,  -- Your air... Your attire... An adventurer, I assume. Have you come looking to register for Conflict?
        LET_ME_INTRODUCE_MYSELF_I_AM_EXCENMILLE_M                               = 7778,  -- Let me introduce myself. I am Excenmille M Aurchiat, acting Conflict Commander of the San d'Orian forces.
        I_HAVE_HEARD_GOOD_THINGS_ABOUT_YOU_YOUR                                 = 7779,  -- I have heard good things about you, %. Your loyalty to the crown is well-renowned throughout the Kingdom.
        I_BELIEVE_THAT_YOU_WOULD_MAKE_A_FINE                                    = 7780,  -- I believe that you would make a fine addition to our ranks, and I welcome you.
        YOU_HAVE_COME_TO_REGISTER_FOR_CONFLICT_HAVE                             = 7781,  -- You have come to register for Conflict, have you not?
        WELL_BEFORE_YOU_MAKE_A_HASTY_DECISION_LET                               = 7782,  -- Well, before you make a hasty decision, let me explain the finer details of what has transpired in recent months.
        IT_ALL_BEGAN_AT_THE_LAST_CONQUEST_EVALUATION                            = 7783,  -- It all began at the last Conquest Evaluation Assembly held in conjunction with the International Commerce Convention. His Majesty, Prince Trion, made the following proposal...
        DO_YOU_UNDERSTAND_I_WAS_WHOM_THE_PRINCE                                 = 7784,  -- Do you understand? I was whom the prince was speaking of. And it is I who believe that your unmatched loyalty, bravery, and ability are necessary for the Kingdom's victory.
        IF_YOU_ARE_TRULY_A_SERVANT_OF_THE                                       = 7785,  -- If you are truly a servant of the crown, you shall not object to raising your sword in the name of the royaulais.
        I_SEE_I_REALIZE_THAT_YOU_ADVENTURERS_HAVE                               = 7786,  -- I see... I realize that you adventurers have other matters that keep you busy. However, do not forget the debt you owe to the Kingdom that provides for you.
        WAIT_A_MINUTE_DON_T_TELL_ME_YOU_2                                       = 7787,  -- Wait a minute, don't tell me... You'rrre one of the Federation's adventurers, right? And you want to sign up for Conflict?
        HMMM_YOUR_RANK_SEEMS_HIGH_ENOUGH_OK_YOU                                 = 7788,  -- Hmmm... Your rank seems high enough... OK! You'rrre in. I could use a veteran like you to whip some of my younger mercenaries into shape.
        MY_NAME_S_MHABI_MOLKOT_UP_UNTIL_A                                       = 7789,  -- My name's Mhabi Molkot. Up until a few days ago, I was Captain of the Terrible Tigresses, the most fearrred group of Mithra Mercenaries in all of Windurst!
        AND_THEN_ALL_OF_A_SUDDEN_THEY_MAKE                                      = 7790,  -- And then all of a sudden, they make me Conflict Commander...
        ANYWAY_I_SAID_YOU_RRRE_IN_SO_YOU                                        = 7791,  -- Anyway, I said you'rrre in, so you'rrre in already! What? Don't tell me you're having second thoughts!
        LET_ME_TELL_YOU_A_LITTLE_ABOUT_WHAT                                     = 7792,  -- Let me tell you a little about what's been going on in the past few months. It all starrrted at some stuffy conference to talk about the conquest...
        AND_THERE_YOU_HAVE_IT_THE_BIGWIGS_UP                                    = 7793,  -- And there you have it. The bigwigs up in the ministries probably hearrrd that I was a professional Conflict player back in my homeland, and entrrrusted me with the reins of this runaway horse.
        MAYBE_IT_S_MY_INSTINCTS_TALKING_BUT_YOU                                 = 7794,  -- Maybe it's my instincts talking, but you look like the type who's dying for a chance at the hunt. What do you say?
        HMPH_WELL_YOU_VE_GOT_GUTS_YOU_RE                                        = 7795,  -- Hmph. Well, you've got guts. You're the first man who's ever turned this cat down./You're turrrning me down?] But I know you'll be back. I can see it in your eyes...
        WHAT_YOU_THINK_YOU_RE_MAN_WOMAN_ENOUGH_2                                = 7796,  -- What!? You think you're man/woman] enough to join our nation's Conflict forces!?
        YOU_THINK_THAT_JUST_BECAUSE_YOU_HAVE_A                                  = 7797,  -- You think that just because you have a few missions under your belt that you're ready to play with the big boys!?
        WELL_SOLDIER_I_VE_SCRAPED_BIGGER_THINGS_THAN                            = 7798,  -- Well, soldier, I've scraped bigger things than you off the bottom of my boot!
        LISTEN_UP_MY_NAME_IS_INVINCIBLE_SHIELD_LEGATUS                          = 7799,  -- Listen up! My name is Invincible Shield, Legatus of the third division of the Republican Legion.
        THE_PRESIDENT_HIMSELF_HAS_MADE_ME_CONFLICT_COMMANDER                    = 7800,  -- The president himself has made me Conflict Commander and put the Bastokan forces under my control. If you join, you will serve under me and under me only!
        WHAT_YOU_HAVE_QUESTIONS_ABOUT_CONFLICT_I_DON                            = 7801,  -- What!? You have questions about Conflict!? I don't remember anyone giving you permission to ask questions, soldier!
        I_WILL_LET_IT_SLIDE_THIS_TIME_BUT                                       = 7802,  -- I will let it slide this time, but it better not happen again! Now, listen up!
        DID_YOU_UNDERSTAND_WHAT_I_JUST_TOLD_YOU                                 = 7803,  -- Did you understand what I just told you!? It is an honor and a privilege to participate in Conflict!
        YOU_WANT_TO_BE_A_HERO_WELL_HERE                                         = 7804,  -- You want to be a hero!? Well, here's your chance, soldier! Sign this application form and you can be on your way!
        MORE_TIME_AND_I_THOUGHT_YOU_WERE_MORE                                   = 7805,  -- More time!? And I thought you were more than just a whining sissy! The Republic doesn't need any more wimps like you! You are dismissed!
        SO_YOU_HAVE_FINALLY_REALIZED_YOUR_DEBT_TO                               = 7806,  -- So, you have finally realized your debt to the Kingdom and decided to repay that debt through service in Conflict?
        WELL_LOOK_WHO_S_BACK_I_KNEW_YOU                                         = 7807,  -- Well, look who's back. I knew you couldn't rrresist the excitement of Conflict. You're ready to sign up, right?
        I_SEE_THAT_YOU_HAVE_FINALLY_COME_TO                                     = 7808,  -- I see that you have finally come to your senses, soldier! Now sign this application and you can be on your way!
        EXCELLENT_HOWEVER_THERE_IS_ONE_LAST_TASK_I                              = 7809,  -- Excellent. However, there is one last task I must ask you to perform before approving your application.
        TRAVEL_TO_BASTOK_AND_WINDURST_AND_MEET_WITH                             = 7810,  -- Travel to Bastok and Windurst and meet with their leaders. You need not worry with the details. They already know you will be coming.
        I_ALSO_WISH_YOU_TO_DELIVER_THESE_LETTERS                                = 7811,  -- I also wish you to deliver these letters to the two nations' Conflict Commanders.
        A_LOFTY_GALKA_GINU_INVINCIBLE_SHIELD_WILL_BE                            = 7812,  -- A lofty Galka, Ginu...Invincible Shield, will be waiting for you in Bastok.
        AND_I_RECALL_THE_COMMANDER_OF_WINDURST_S                                = 7813,  -- And I recall the Commander of Windurst's forces was a Mithra named Mhabi...something-or-other. I have such trouble remembering foreign names.
        THAT_IS_ALL_YOU_MAY_SET_OFF_IMMEDIATELY                                 = 7814,  -- That is all. You may set off immediately. I must say, I am quite honored to send such a fine adventurer as yourself to represent the Kingdom.
        WONDERFUL_I_KNOW_YOU_RRRE_READY_TO_GET                                  = 7815,  -- Wonderful! I know you'rrre ready to get out there and starrrt fighting right away, but before you do, you'rrre going to need a license.
        TO_GET_A_LICENSE_YOU_LL_NEED_TO                                         = 7816,  -- To get a license, you'll need to meet the leaders of the other two nations.
        AND_YOU_THOUGHT_THAT_WAS_IT_YOU_LL                                      = 7817,  -- And--you thought that was it?--you'll need to take these letters to the Conflict Commanders of San d'Oria and Bastok.
        I_DON_T_KNOW_MUCH_ABOUT_THE_TWO                                         = 7818,  -- I don't know much about the two, but the Commander of Bastok is some thousand-year-old gut-busterrr named Invincible Shield. I think I rememberrr the one from San d'Oria being some cold-blooded Elvaan named Excenmille.
        NOW_GET_GOING_THE_FASTER_YOU_GET_THIS                                   = 7819,  -- Now get going! The faster you get this done, the quicker you can be exchanging blows with those boneheads from the other nations!
        HEH_HEH_HEH_WHEN_THEY_SEE_WHO_I                                         = 7820,  -- Heh heh heh... When they see who I've sent to them, they'll be shaking in their greaves!
        YOU_VE_MADE_THE_RIGHT_CHOICE_SOLDIER_FROM                               = 7821,  -- You've made the right choice, soldier! From this day on, you are an official member of the Bastokan Conflict forces!
        NOW_LISTEN_UP_BECAUSE_I_M_ABOUT_TO                                      = 7822,  -- Now listen up, because I'm about to give you your first orders, and I'm only going to say them once! You are to infiltrate the enemies' cities and meet with their leaders!
        WHAT_WHO_ARE_THE_ENEMY_WHERE_HAVE_YOU                                   = 7823,  -- What!? Who are the enemy? Where have you been the last twenty-five years, living in a hole!? The enemy are the Elvaan and the Tarutaru!
        AFTER_MEETING_WITH_THEIR_LEADERS_YOU_ARE_TO                             = 7824,  -- After meeting with their leaders, you are to deliver these correspondences to the Conflict Commanders of those nations! Don't worry, you'll have no trouble finding those half-rate cowards!
        LOOK_FOR_EXCENMILLE_IN_SAN_D_ORIA_AND                                   = 7825,  -- Look for Excenmille in San d'Oria and Mhabi in Windurst! Just the sound of their names makes me want to puke!
        YOU_HAVE_YOUR_ORDERS_NOW_MAKE_YOUR_FINAL                                = 7826,  -- You have your orders, now make your final preparations and be on your way! You have ten, no, eight minutes! Dismissed!!!
        IS_SOMETHING_THE_MATTER_YOU_ARE_TO_MEET                                 = 7827,  -- Is something the matter? You are to meet the leaders of Bastok and Windurst.
        ALSO_GIVE_THE_LETTERS_I_HANDED_YOU_TO                                   = 7828,  -- Also, give the letters I handed you to the Conflict Commanders Invincible Shield and Mhabi...something-or-other.
        WHAT_S_WRONG_HURRY_UP_AND_MEET_THE                                      = 7829,  -- What's wrong? Hurry up and meet the leaders of Bastok and San d'Oria.
        OH_AND_DON_T_FORRRGET_TO_GIVE_MY                                        = 7830,  -- Oh, and don't forrrget to give my letters to Invincible Shield and Excenmille.
        DON_T_EVEN_TELL_ME_THAT_YOU_FORGOT                                      = 7831,  -- Don't even tell me that you forgot your orders! I've met tunnel worms with better memories than you!
        NOW_LISTEN_UP_SOLDIER_AFTER_MEETING_WITH_THE                            = 7832,  -- Now listen up, soldier! After meeting with the leaders of San d'Oria and Windurst, you are to deliver the correspondences I handed you to the Conflict Commanders Excenmille and Mhabi Molkot! And I don't want to see your pathetic face until you've completed your mission! Dismissed!!!
