        ON_NORTHERN_QUON_LIES_THE_WALLED_CAPITAL_OF                             = 11118,  -- On northern Quon lies the walled capital of the Kingdom of San d'Oria.
        HOME_TO_FABLED_WARRIORS_KNOWN_AS_ROYAL_KNIGHTS                          = 11119,  -- Home to fabled warriors known as Royal Knights, she is a land where strength of arms rules over all.
        YET_HER_OBSESSION_WITH_MIGHT_HAS_WIDENED_THE                            = 11120,  -- Yet, her obsession with might has widened the gap between San d'Oria and the advanced industries and economies of its neighbors.
        PTTHE_FORTRESS_CITY_OF_SAN_D_ORIA_LIES                                  = 11122,  -- PTThe fortress city of San d'Oria lies to the north on the great continent of Quon. The beating heart of an ancient kingdom, it is home to a thousand legends past.
        PTBUT_NOW_HER_REIGN_OF_GLORY_IS_BUT                                     = 11123,  -- PTBut now, her reign of glory is but a memory. Heroes raise shining swords to the heavens no more.
        PTTHE_SUN_HAS_SET_ON_THE_KINGDOM_OF                                     = 11124,  -- PTThe sun has set on the kingdom of knights. An old lion, never to rise again... Thus do some dismiss her now.
        PTYET_YOUNG_ELVAAN_KNIGHTS_STILL_VENTURE_PROUDLY_INTO                   = 11125,  -- PTYet young Elvaan knights still venture proudly into the wilds of Vana'diel, determined to triumph over any foe.
        PTON_THIS_PARTICULAR_DAY_THERE_COMES_A_NEW                              = 11126,  -- PTOn this particular day there comes a new adventurer, ready to make a name for himself/herself] in San d'Oria.
        PTTHE_KING_WISHES_TO_BOLSTER_HIS_RANKS_AND                              = 11127,  -- PTThe king wishes to bolster his ranks, and % has journeyed far to answer the call.
        PTSHOULD_FORTUNE_FAVOR_HIM_HER_BARDS_ACROSS_THE                         = 11128,  -- PTShould fortune favor him/her], bards across the land will sing of his/her] exploits for generations to come.
        PTOF_COURSE_HE_SHE_HAS_ONLY_BEGUN_HIS                                   = 11129,  -- PTOf course, he/she] has only begun his/her] rise to glory. No one can tell what his/her] future holds.
        PTNEVER_BEFORE_HAS_HE_SHE_SET_FOOT_WITHIN                               = 11130,  -- PTNever before has he/she] set foot within the Elvaan capital, but he/she] is resolved to let nothing stand in his/her] way.
        I_SAY_WATCH_WHERE_YOU_RE_GOING                                          = 11131,  -- I say! Watch where you're going!
        OH_A_NEW_RECRUIT_ARE_YOU_THAT_EXPLAINS                                  = 11132,  -- Oh, a new recruit, are you? That explains it!
        WELL_FAR_BE_IT_FROM_ME_TO_CHASTISE                                      = 11133,  -- Well, far be it from me to chastise someone on his/her] first day. Still, as a citizen of San d'Oria, you--
        AH_NONTERENE_WHAT_ARE_YOU_DOING_HERE                                    = 11134,  -- Ah, Nonterene! What are you doing here?
        PRINCE_TRION_I_WAS_EXPLAINING_TO_THIS_RECRUIT                           = 11135,  -- Prince Trion, I was explaining to this recruit here about what it means to be a proud citizen of San d'Oria!
        A_RECRUIT_STRENGTHEN_YOUR_SWORD_ARM_AND_YOUR                            = 11136,  -- A recruit? Strengthen your sword arm and your stature as a knight. Thus will you best serve the glory of our great kingdom.
        SAN_D_ORIA_HAS_MORE_THAN_ENOUGH_SOLDIERS                                = 11137,  -- San d'Oria has more than enough soldiers already, brother. Speaking of which, should you not be training them, instead of bothering new recruits with talk of war?
        YOU_ARE_TOO_BOLD                                                        = 11138,  -- You are too bold!
        REALLY_PIEUJE_IS_THAT_ANY_WAY_TO_SPEAK                                  = 11139,  -- Really, Pieuje! Is that any way to speak to your brother?
        I_VE_SAID_THE_TRUTH_NOTHING_MORE_THE                                    = 11140,  -- I've said the truth, nothing more. The ranks of our armies could swell to bursting, and victory would still be far.
        IT_IS_YOUR_HEAD_THAT_IS_SWOLLEN_BROTHER                                 = 11141,  -- It is your head that is swollen, brother. With enough numbers, we could crush the beastmen! And without having to resort to your misguided tactics!
        MY_TACTICS_MISGUIDED_OH_THAT_IS_RICH_TELL                               = 11142,  -- My tactics, misguided? Oh, that is rich! Tell me of the tactics that lost an entire company in Batallia Downs the other day?
        IT_S_GOOD_YOU_RE_SO_FOND_OF                                             = 11143,  -- It's good you're so fond of talking, as I've never seen you wield a sword! Better to shout orders from the rear than reveal your ineptitude in actual combat!
        STOP_YOUR_QUARRELING_BOTH_OF_YOU                                        = 11144,  -- Stop your quarreling, both of you!
        A_DIVIDED_LEADERSHIP_ONLY_CREATES_UNREST_AMONG_THE                      = 11145,  -- A divided leadership only creates unrest among the people, soldier and civilian alike. Surely you are both aware of this?
        OH_I_SUPPOSE_I_WARN_YOU_PIEUJE_TALK                                     = 11146,  -- Oh, I suppose. I warn you, Pieuje, talk to me that way again and I won't be so forgiving.
        GOOD_OLD_TRION_THREATS_OF_VIOLENCE_ARE_HIS                              = 11147,  -- Good old Trion. Threats of violence are his only recourse when a conversation does not go his way. Like a child, he is!
        THEY_ARE_BOTH_LIKE_CHILDREN_QUICK_TO_INSULT                             = 11148,  -- They are both like children, quick to insult and quicker to take offense! Really...
        I_MUST_APOLOGIZE_FOR_THAT_BUT_OURS_IS                                   = 11149,  -- I must apologize for that. But ours is truly a great kingdom, and I expect you to further her glory.
        THOSE_TWO_ARE_A_HANDFUL_BUT_THEY_TRULY                                  = 11150,  -- Those two are a handful, but they truly are the closest of brothers.
        YOU_SEEM_LOST_RECRUIT_TELL_ME_IF_THERE                                  = 11151,  -- You seem lost, recruit. Tell me if there's anything you wish to know.
        SOMETHING_YOU_D_LIKE_TO_KNOW_NOTHING_IN                                 = 11152,  -- Something you'd like to know? Nothing in particular. I want to go out and fight! I want to go shopping. I want to know more about adventuring.
        JUST_ARRIVED_AND_YOU_RE_ALREADY_ACHING_TO                               = 11153,  -- Just arrived and you're already aching to leave, eh? Listen, the land is wild beyond our gates, filled with fiends and their ilk.
        IF_YOU_MUST_GO_OUTSIDE_HEAD_THROUGH_RANPERRE                            = 11154,  -- If you must go outside, head through Ranperre Gate. Allow me to explain.
        RIGHT_NOW_WE_RE_ON_THE_PARADE_GROUNDS                                   = 11155,  -- Right now we're on the Parade Grounds. Find the gate to the west.
        STEP_THROUGH_AND_PASS_THE_FURNITURE_STORE_AND                           = 11156,  -- Step through and pass the furniture store and the inn. Take the gate on the left.
        MAKE_ANOTHER_LEFT_DOWN_THE_STAIRS_YOU_LL                                = 11157,  -- Make another left down the stairs. You'll see Ranperre Gate beyond.
        SHOULD_YOU_NEED_DIRECTIONS_ASK_THOSE_AROUND_YOU                         = 11158,  -- Should you need directions, ask those around you. Our citizens are friendly, for the most part.
        WAIT_WAIT_ONE_MORE_THING_IF_SOMEONE_AIDS                                = 11159,  -- Wait, wait--one more thing. If someone aids you, be sure to show them your gratitude. That is all.
        FOR_WEAPONS_AND_BASIC_SUPPLIES_TAKE_A_WALK                              = 11160,  -- For weapons and basic supplies, take a walk through the city and you'll find all that you need.
        RECRUITS_DON_T_KNOW_WHICH_WAY_TO_HOLD                                   = 11161,  -- Recruits... Don't know which way to hold a sword and you think you're ready. Well, what would you like to know?
        YOU_REALLY_ARE_A_HANDFUL_YOU_NEED_TO                                    = 11162,  -- You really are a handful! You need to go to Novice's Hall. Head through Victory Arch, across the courtyard, and through the gate you'll see on the right.
        WHAT_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_KNOW_ABOUT_HELPING                               = 11163,  -- What would you like to know about? Helping people. Hunting monsters. Making easy money. Working for my country.
        AH_A_COMMENDABLE_CHOICE_I_SAW_A_LADY                                    = 11164,  -- Ah, a commendable choice! I saw a lady in front of a house on Pikeman's Way who may be in need of assistance.
        NOVICES_DON_T_KNOW_YOUR_OWN_LIMITS_UNTIL                                = 11165,  -- Novices... Don't know your own limits until a fiend beats it into your head for you. Very well. How about gathering some hides for the Tanners' Guild in Southern San d'Oria?
        SOUTHERN_SAN_D_ORIA_IS_JUST_BEYOND_VICTORY                              = 11166,  -- Southern San d'Oria is just beyond Victory Arch there. Pass through and go west. You'll find the Tanners' Guild soon enough.
        EASY_MONEY_EH_TYPICAL_I_CAN_T_PROMISE                                   = 11167,  -- Easy money, eh? Typical! I can't promise ease, but check the lumberyard on Laborman's Way. They should have some work for you.
        GO_THROUGH_THE_GATE_TO_THE_WEST_AND                                     = 11168,  -- Go through the gate to the west and pass the Phoenix Perch Inn. You should see another gate there to your right. That gate leads to Laborman's Way.
        AH_A_COMMENDABLE_CHOICE_EACH_ENTRANCE_TO_THE                            = 11169,  -- Ah, a commendable choice! Each entrance to the city has a gatehouse. Tell the guards there you wish to work for the glory of the Kingdom!
        HERE_TAKE_THIS_IT_S_AN_ADVENTURER_COUPON                                = 11170,  -- Here, take this. It's an adventurer coupon. Give it to Matildie in front of Chateau d'Oraguille.
        TO_HAND_ITEMS_TO_OTHERS_SELECT_TRADE_FROM                               = 11171,  -- To hand items to others, select Trade from the main menu. That should be easy enough for a new recruit to understand.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT                                                        = 11172,  -- What do you want?
        AH_A_NEW_RECRUIT_WHAT_ARE_YOU_DOING                                     = 11173,  -- Ah, a new recruit! What are you doing in the city? Get out there and slay some fiends! That's where the money is!
        SPEAKING_OF_MONEY_I_HAVEN_T_SEEN_THAT                                   = 11174,  -- Speaking of money, I haven't seen that gambler all day. Has he run off again?
        YOU_KNOW_HIM_I_RECKON_HE_S_OUT                                          = 11175,  -- You know him. I reckon he's out scouring the Parade Grounds for suckers with gil to wager.
        WHO_DOES_HE_THINK_HE_IS_RUNNING_OFF                                     = 11176,  -- Who does he think he is, running off when we've piles of work to do! I'll give him a good lashing when he gets back!
        GAMBLING_IS_THE_RUIN_OF_MANY_I_TELL                                     = 11177,  -- Gambling is the ruin of many, I tell you...
        A_GAMBLER_OH_YOU_MEAN_VARCHET_HE_WENT                                   = 11178,  -- A gambler? Oh, you mean Varchet. He went strolling through Victory Arch just a while ago.
        HE_S_PROBABLY_AT_SOME_TAVERN_BY_NOW                                     = 11179,  -- He's probably at some tavern by now. You'd best stay away from gamblers like him.
        HE_WAS_A_KNIGHT_ONCE_AND_ALWAYS_LOVED                                   = 11180,  -- He was a knight, once, and always loved games of chance. They say his habit eventually cost him his knighthood.
        HEY_IT_S_THAT_RECRUIT_FROM_BEFORE_SO                                    = 11181,  -- Hey, it's that recruit from before. So you're the one who got Varchet to show up again!
        I_DON_T_REMEMBER_ASKING_YOU_TO_FETCH                                    = 11182,  -- I don't remember asking you to fetch him, but I owe you my thanks anyway. Here, take this!
        EH_THAT_GAMBLER_VARCHET_AYE_HE_WAS_JUST                                 = 11183,  -- Eh? That gambler, Varchet? Aye, he was just here.
        VARCHET_I_GAVE_HIM_A_PROPER_LASHING_FOR                                 = 11184,  -- Varchet? I gave him a proper lashing for what he did, and then he ran off again! He's not to be trusted, that one.
        A_MAGIC_SHOP_YOU_SAY_A_BIT_OF                                           = 11185,  -- A magic shop, you say? A bit of magic would come in handy... I know! I'll have my daughter study it for me!
        WEARY_TRAVELER_COME_PRAY_WITH_US                                        = 11186,  -- Weary traveler, come pray with us.
        HERE_IN_THE_SAN_D_ORIA_CATHEDRAL_WE                                     = 11187,  -- Here in the San d'Oria Cathedral, we devote our lives to helping people reach the shining gates of Paradise.
        SHOULD_YOU_WISH_TO_KNOW_MORE_ABOUT_PARADISE                             = 11188,  -- Should you wish to know more about Paradise, come to the vicasque's sermon. Much will be revealed.
        SHOULD_YOU_WISH_TO_HEAR_THE_SERMON_PLEASE                               = 11189,  -- Should you wish to hear the sermon, please prepare an offering of % as proof of your faith.
        YOU_WILL_NEED_TO_BRING_THE_WATER_PLEASE                                 = 11190,  -- You will need % to bring the water. Please beseech the friar who stands thither.
        WELCOME_I_DISTRIBUTE_MATERIAL_GOODS_FOR_VISITORS_TO                     = 11191,  -- Welcome. I distribute material goods for visitors to our cathedral.
        SHOULD_YOU_SEEK_STEP_FORTH_I_HUMBLY_ASK                                 = 11192,  -- Should you seek %, step forth! I humbly ask for a donation of 10 gil.
        MAKE_A_DONATION_YES_OF_COURSE_NO_I                                      = 11193,  -- Make a donation? Yes, of course. No, I will not.
        YOU_DONATE_10_GIL                                                       = 11194,  -- You donate 10 gil.
        TAKE_THIS_TO_EAST_RONFAURE_TRADE_IT_TO                                  = 11195,  -- Take this % to East Ronfaure. Trade it to the Cheval River to draw its hallowed water!
        MAY_PARADISE_OPEN_ITS_GATES_TO_YOU                                      = 11196,  -- May Paradise open its gates to you.
        THAT_IS_UNFORTUNATE_TRULY_UNFORTUNATE                                   = 11197,  -- That is unfortunate. Truly unfortunate...
        PRESENT_THAT_TO_MIAGEAU_STANDS_HE_AT_THE                                = 11198,  -- Present that % to Miageau. Stands he at the portal.
        ADMIRABLE_IS_YOUR_GENEROSITY_BUT_THIS_IS_NOT                            = 11199,  -- Admirable is your generosity, but this is not % .
        THANK_YOU_SACRED_IS_THE_YOU_CONVEYED_HITHER                             = 11200,  -- Thank you. Sacred is the % you conveyed hither.
        IN_TESTAMENT_TO_YOUR_DEVOTION_I_GIVE_YOU                                = 11201,  -- In testament to your devotion, I give you this %. Through it, Altana's providence is yours.
        THE_CHEVAL_RUNS_THROUGH_EAST_RONFAURE_EXIT_THE                          = 11202,  -- The Cheval runs through East Ronfaure. Exit the city through the Eastgate, and head north until you come to a small bridge over the river.
        STAND_UPON_THE_BRIDGE_IN_PEACE_THEN_TRADE                               = 11203,  -- Stand upon the bridge in peace... Then trade your % to draw the sacred water!
        ONCE_YOU_HAVE_RETURN_TO_ME_MIAGEAU                                      = 11204,  -- Once you have %, return to me, Miageau.
        MY_SON_CHILD_YOUR_OFFERING_OF_WAS_GENEROUS                              = 11205,  -- My son/child], your offering of % was generous enough. You need not obtain another waterskin.
        OH_WHERE_COULD_HE_BE                                                    = 11206,  -- Oh, where could he be?
        I_I_CAME_HERE_WITH_MY_FATHER_AND                                        = 11207,  -- I-I came here with my father, and now he's g-gone!
        MY_FATHER_IS_A_KNIGHT_TODAY_HE_S                                        = 11208,  -- My father is a knight! Today he's on holiday, and so we went out for a walk. B-but now...
        M_MY_FATHER_IS_SO_PROUD_OF_HIS                                          = 11209,  -- M-my father is so proud of his knighthood, he's still in uniform today. He looks noble indeed, though his armor creaks with each step!
        HE_S_NOT_WEARING_HIS_HELMET_THOUGH_WE                                   = 11210,  -- He's not wearing his helmet, though... We came through Victory Arch together but, but now...
        OH_FATHER_WHERE_ARE_YOU                                                 = 11211,  -- Oh, Father! Where are you?
        WHAT_S_THAT_MY_SON_AT_THE_PARADE                                        = 11212,  -- What's that? My son, at the Parade Grounds, crying? I'm busy here, so could you let him know I'll go as soon as I'm done?
        WHAT_Y_YOU_FOUND_MY_FATHER                                              = 11213,  -- What? Y-you found my father?
        AILBECHE                                                                = 11214,  -- Ailbeche?
        FATHER                                                                  = 11215,  -- Father?
        WHY_YOU_MILKSOP_LOSE_SIGHT_OF_YOUR_FATHER                               = 11216,  -- Why, you milksop! Lose sight of your father and all you do is wail for the nearest stranger? Have you no shame?
        B_BUT_FATHER                                                            = 11217,  -- B-but, Father...
        ENOUGH_YOU_ARE_ELVAAN_I_EXPECT_MORE_FROM                                = 11218,  -- Enough! You are Elvaan! I expect more from you! Understand?
        B_BUT_FATHER_NO                                                         = 11219,  -- B-but, Father! No...
        I_LL_FORGE_YOU_INTO_SHAPE_YET_NOW                                       = 11220,  -- I'll forge you into shape yet! Now, stand there till you get a hold of yourself!
        NO_FATHER_DON_T_LEAVE_ME                                                = 11221,  -- No, Father! Don't leave me!
        LET_ME_APOLOGIZE_FOR_MY_SON_PLEASE_ACCEPT                               = 11222,  -- Let me apologize for my son. Please accept this in return for your time.
        NO_TH_THAT_S_MY_FISHING_ROD_FATHER                                      = 11223,  -- No! Th-that's my fishing rod... Father!
        QUIET_I_WILL_NOT_HAVE_MY_OWN_SON                                        = 11224,  -- Quiet! I will not have my own son cry like a baby!
        GOOD_DAY_ADVENTURER                                                     = 11225,  -- Good day, adventurer!
        CONFOUND_IT_WHAT_AM_I_TO_DO                                             = 11226,  -- Confound it! What am I to do?
        WHAT_S_THE_MATTER_MONTAUBE_WHY_AREN_T                                   = 11227,  -- What's the matter, Montaube? Why aren't you cooking supper for the guests?
        THAT_S_JUST_THE_PROBLEM_I_STARTED_THE                                   = 11228,  -- That's just the problem! I started the soup, see, and then I realized I've no batagreens! The broth is but water without it!
        NOW_THAT_S_ODD_JUST_THIS_MORNING_I                                      = 11229,  -- Now that's odd. Just this morning, I asked Boncort to fetch one...
        BON_BON                                                                 = 11230,  -- Bon-bon!
        YES_MASTER_ABEAULE                                                      = 11231,  -- Yes, Master Abeaule?
        WHERE_ARE_THE_BATAGREENS_I_ASKED_FOR                                    = 11232,  -- Where are the batagreens I asked for?
        OH_I_FORGOT_TO_TELL_YOU_THE_GROCER                                      = 11233,  -- Oh, I forgot to tell you! The grocer said his herb-man ran into Orcs, so he couldn't get any today!
        I_SEARCHED_EVERY_STALL_IN_THE_CITY_BUT                                  = 11234,  -- I searched every stall in the city, but there wasn't a sprig to be found! Honest!
        WELL_HOW_CAN_I_MAKE_MY_SHEEP_HEAD                                       = 11235,  -- Well, how can I make my sheep-head stew without batagreens?
        BON_BON_GO_TRACK_DOWN_THIS_HERB_MAN                                     = 11236,  -- Bon-bon, go track down this herb-man yourself!
        DO_YOU_THINK_I_M_MAD_WHO_WOULD                                          = 11237,  -- Do you think I'm mad? Who would greet the guests if Orcs got me?
        NOW_NOW_SIMMER_DOWN_LADS                                                = 11238,  -- Now, now... Simmer down, lads.
        SIR_MADAM_YOU_RE_AN_ADVENTURER_ARE_YOU                                  = 11239,  -- Sir/Madam], you're an adventurer, are you not? We can't leave the city with fiends on the road, so we need your help.
        OUR_TRADER_A_SUPPLIER_OF_FRESH_PRODUCE_WORKS                            = 11240,  -- Our trader, a supplier of fresh produce, works from a tower on the southern edge of West Ronfaure. Might you procure % for us?
        OF_COURSE_YOU_LL_BE_PAID_FOR_YOUR                                       = 11241,  -- Of course, you'll be paid for your time. What do you say?
        WELL_I_ACCEPT_I_MUST_DECLINE                                            = 11242,  -- Well? I accept. I must decline.
        AH_TOO_BAD_YOU_GOT_MY_HOPES_UP                                          = 11243,  -- Ah, too bad, You got my hopes up.
        SO_YOU_VE_HAD_A_CHANGE_OF_HEART                                         = 11244,  -- So, you've had a change of heart, have you?
        SPLENDID_TAKE_THIS_TO_PHAIRET_HE_S_IN                                   = 11245,  -- Splendid! Take this % to Phairet. He's in a tower far south into West Ronfaure. He'll hand you % in return!
        WE_ALWAYS_PAY_AFTER_DELIVERY_SO_YOU_NEEDN                               = 11246,  -- We always pay after delivery, so you needn't give him any money!
        BRING_BACK_THAT_AS_QUICK_AS_YOU_CAN                                     = 11247,  -- Bring back that % as quick as you can, eh? And don't drop the %, either!
        YOU_VE_LOST_IT_NO_IT_S_RIGHT                                            = 11248,  -- You've lost it? No, it's right here! Sorry...
        AH_THAT_S_A_RELIEF                                                      = 11249,  -- Ah, that's a relief.
        FOR_THE_LOVE_OF_AH_WELL_I_SUPPOSE                                       = 11250,  -- For the love of--! Ah, well, I suppose I can write you up another one. Don't you lose it again, now!
        SORRY_NO_TIME_TO_CHAT_I_VE_YET                                          = 11251,  -- Sorry, no time to chat! I've yet to finish cleaning the rooms.
        BEGGING_YOUR_PARDON_SIR_MADAM_BUT_I_M                                   = 11252,  -- Begging your pardon, sir/madam], but I'm cooking right now. If you've got something for me, it'll just have to wait.
        OOOH_THIS_IS_A_FINE_FIT_FOR_OUR                                         = 11253,  -- Oooh, this is a fine %! Fit for our guests' soup!
        HERE_THIS_IS_YOURS_FOR_YOUR_TROUBLE_THANK                               = 11254,  -- Here, this is yours for your trouble. Thank you!
        YOU_RE_MY_FAVORITE_ADVENTURER_THANKS_AGAIN_FOR                          = 11255,  -- You're my favorite adventurer! Thanks again for your help!
        EH_WHAT_S_THIS_I_VE_NO_NEED                                             = 11256,  -- Eh, what's this? I've no need of this clutter.
        WELCOME_WEARY_TRAVELER_THE_VICASQUE_WILL_SOON_BEGIN                     = 11257,  -- Welcome, weary traveler. The vicasque will soon begin today's sermon.
        HAVE_YOU_COME_TO_HEAR_THE_SERMON_GOOD                                   = 11258,  -- Have you come to hear the sermon? Good, the vicasque will begin soon.
        BELIEVERS_TODAY_S_SERMON_WILL_NOW_BEGIN                                 = 11259,  -- Believers, today's sermon will now begin.
        KINDLY_REFLECT_UPON_HIS_WORDS_IN_SILENCE                                = 11260,  -- Kindly reflect upon his words in silence.
        ALL_OF_ALTANA_S_CHILDREN_ARE_WELCOME_HERE                               = 11261,  -- All of Altana's children are welcome here.
        IS_THIS_YOUR_FIRST_TIME_HERE_JOIN_US                                    = 11262,  -- Is this your first time here? Join us in prayer!
        PARADISE_IS_A_PLACE_WITHOUT_FEAR_WITHOUT_DEATH                          = 11263,  -- Paradise is a place without fear, without death!
        PAPSQUE_SHAMONDE_SOMETIMES_ADDRESSES_THE_CITY_FROM_THE                  = 11264,  -- Papsque Shamonde sometimes addresses the city from the balcony, you know. I long for his blessing, if but once!
        WITH_EACH_SERMON_I_TAKE_ANOTHER_STEP_CLOSER                             = 11265,  -- With each sermon, I take another step closer to Paradise.
        TRULY_FORTUNATE_ARE_WE_THAT_WORDS_OF_SACRAMENT                          = 11266,  -- Truly fortunate are we that words of sacrament are read every day!
        GODDESS_ABOVE_DELIVER_US_TO_PARADISE                                    = 11267,  -- Goddess above, deliver us to Paradise!
        I_SHALL_BEGIN_SHORTLY_SHOULD_YOU_HAVE_QUESTIONS                         = 11268,  -- I shall begin shortly. Should you have questions, kindly beseech the friar at the narthex.
        MY_CHILDREN_WELCOME_TODAY_I_WOULD_LIKE_TO                               = 11269,  -- My children, welcome. Today I would like to speak about Paradise.
        IN_THIS_WORLD_WE_ARE_BORN_TO_WITHER                                     = 11270,  -- In this world, we are born to wither and die. Every mortal is bound by these chains.
        ONLY_THE_CHOSEN_MAY_PASS_THROUGH_THE_GATES                              = 11271,  -- Only the chosen may pass through the gates of Paradise, to live forever under Altana, free from fear and decay.
        HERE_IN_THE_SAN_D_ORIA_CATHEDRAL_WE_2                                   = 11272,  -- Here in the San d'Oria Cathedral, we devote each day to helping believers along the blessed path.
        THOUGH_THE_ROAD_TO_PARADISE_IS_FRAUGHT_WITH                             = 11273,  -- Though the road to Paradise is fraught with peril, there is no other way to life everlasting.
        ALTANA_HAS_GUIDED_US_HERE_TODAY_TOWARD_THE                              = 11274,  -- Altana has guided us here today. Toward the gates of Paradise we walk together, one step at a time.
        MY_CHILDREN_AS_YOU_PREPARE_TO_TAKE_YOUR                                 = 11275,  -- My children, as you prepare to take your first step, remember that naught is as important as the spirit of giving.
        PROVIDENCE_SHALL_COME_WITH_THE_RENUNCIATION_OF_GREED                    = 11276,  -- Providence shall come with the renunciation of greed. The one treasure we may keep is generosity!
        NOW_I_RECALL_A_FRIAR_ON_RETREAT_IN                                      = 11277,  -- Now, I recall a friar on retreat in East Ronfaure.
        HE_SPENDS_HIS_DAYS_FASTING_IN_PRAYER_PAUSING                            = 11278,  -- He spends his days fasting in prayer, pausing only to eat blue peas.
        IN_REVERENCE_OF_HIS_DEVOTION_LET_US_DELIVER                             = 11279,  -- In reverence of his devotion, let us deliver him sustenance!
        BESEECH_FRIAR_ABIOLEGET_AT_THE_NARTHEX_SO_THAT                          = 11280,  -- Beseech Friar Abioleget at the narthex, so that he might entrust the peas to you.
        ESCHEW_ALL_DESIRE_GIVE_YOURSELF_TO_ALTANA_AND                           = 11281,  -- Eschew all desire, give yourself to Altana, and she will bless you in her glory.
        AND_WITH_THESE_WORDS_I_SEND_YOU_MAY                                     = 11282,  -- And with these words, I send you. May her light shine upon you, always.
        I_WILL_PROVIDE_YOU_WITH_FOR_A_PITTANCE                                  = 11283,  -- I will provide you with % for a pittance of # gil.
        TAKE_YOU_THIS_WITHIN_A_TOWER_IN_EAST                                    = 11284,  -- Take you this %. Within a tower in East Ronfaure shall you find the friar.
        YOU_SHALL_CARRY_THE_PEAS_TO_THE_FRIAR                                   = 11285,  -- You shall carry the peas to the friar, and return hither.
        WE_RECOGNIZE_YOUR_CONVICTION_TODAY_YOU_ARE_A                            = 11286,  -- We recognize your conviction. Today, you are a step closer to Paradise!
        TO_HONOR_YOUR_DEVOTION_I_BESTOW_UPON_YOU                                = 11287,  -- To honor your devotion, I bestow upon you this blessing.
        SEE_FRIAR_ABIOLEGET_AT_THE_NARTHEX_SO_HE                                = 11288,  -- See Friar Abioleget at the narthex so he may hear of your service. Quickly, now!
        GO_NOW_MY_CHILD_KNOW_IN_YOUR_HEART                                      = 11289,  -- Go now, my child. Know in your heart that Altana watches over you.
        THIS_IS_THE_ENTRANCE_TO_THE_WATCHTOWER_WHICH                            = 11290,  -- This is the entrance to the watchtower, which overlooks the woods of Ronfaure.
        YOU_RE_ON_WATCH_TODAY_WHAT_S_THE                                        = 11291,  -- You're on watch today? What's the password, then?
        YOU_RE_NEW_HERE_AREN_T_YOU_FIRST                                        = 11292,  -- You're new here, aren't you? First, target me, then type /pass password Where password is the password, get it?
        THAT_S_GOOD_ENOUGH_FOR_ME_FOLLOW_THE                                    = 11293,  -- That's good enough for me. Follow the guard's instructions once you're inside, and you'll do fine.
        V_7                                                                     = 11294,  -- %`V]%7||
        THAT_S_NOT_IT_BETTER_GO_ASK_AGAIN                                       = 11295,  -- That's not it. Better go ask again, eh?
        M_H_FFB                                                                 = 11296,  -- ($%=)%">M h*FfB
        TH_ISADI_P5_Q_S_IR_H_D                                                  = 11297,  -- tH%IsADi %%/(p5="q>*%!s/iR*"H-D"AD=q>B
        ID_1E_I_IQ_1KV_M_D_DY5_Q                                                = 11298,  -- ;1E%=I#]* iq>%% #%1kV M/D+DY5"q>B
        KQ_QF_A_H_JH_H                                                          = 11299,  -- `?kq%?qF%$%>%A%h%-jH")H
        A_IF_OM_TH_1_I_IM8_G                                                    = 11301,  -- ((%a)if%%OM %%tH%1)I "iM8>)g
        GREETINGS_FAITHFUL_ONE_HAVE_YOU_COME_TO_HEAR                            = 11302,  -- Greetings, faithful one. Have you come to hear the vicasque's sermons? Indeed they are the surest way to Paradise.
        I_STUDY_SCRIPTURE_SO_THAT_I_TOO_MAY                                     = 11303,  -- I study scripture so that I, too, may one day give sermons like Vicasque Arnau.
        IN_THIS_CHAMBER_WE_STUDY_THE_TEACHINGS_OF                               = 11304,  -- In this chamber we study the teachings of Altana. Through years of prayer and devotion have we earned this right.
        BY_THE_WAY_I_HAVE_HEARD_OF_YOUR                                         = 11305,  -- By the way, I have heard of your deeds, and I would ask of you a trivial favor.
        ONE_OF_OUR_ORDER_IS_ON_RETREAT_AT                                       = 11306,  -- One of our order is on retreat at the Crag of Holla. Might you take him scrolls for his next circle?
        HOW_UNFORTUNATE_I_FEAR_YOUR_PLACE_IN_PARADISE                           = 11307,  -- How unfortunate! I fear your place in Paradise may be in jeopardy.
        GREAT_IS_THE_GENEROSITY_IN_YOUR_HEART_TAKE                              = 11308,  -- Great is the generosity in your heart! Take % and carry it to Friar Faurbellant at the Crag of Holla.
        FRIAR_FAURBELLANT_IS_ON_RETREAT_AT_THE_CRAG                             = 11309,  -- Friar Faurbellant is on retreat at the Crag of Holla. Please give % to him.
        GRACIOUS_ARE_WE_FOR_YOUR_SERVICE_RECEIVE_THIS                           = 11310,  -- Gracious are we for your service. Receive this as acknowledgment of your devotion.
        FRIARS_SPEND_EVERY_DAY_IN_ASCETIC_TRAINING_GREET                        = 11311,  -- Friars spend every day in ascetic training. Greet them kindly; it will inspire them to strive ever harder.
        HOW_MAY_I_HELP_YOU                                                      = 11312,  -- How may I help you?
        I_M_IN_A_HURRY_MY_GOOD_FELLOW                                           = 11313,  -- I'm in a hurry, my good fellow! I need five iron swords, and quick!
        I_CAN_ONLY_DO_WHAT_I_CAN_DO                                             = 11314,  -- I can only do what I can do, no more.
        I_WAS_ORDERED_BY_THE_CAPTAIN_HIMSELF_WE                                 = 11315,  -- I was ordered by the captain himself! We're sending a force to Batallia Downs tomorrow, and they need blades!
        I_DON_T_CARE_WHO_S_ORDERED_WHAT                                         = 11316,  -- I don't care who's ordered what! I can't make blades without iron, now, can I? If you want them that badly, bring me metal!
        STOP_IT_RIGHT_NOW_THE_BOTH_OF_YOU                                       = 11317,  -- Stop it right now, the both of you. This is a place of business!
        HMPH_YOU_RE_RIGHT_BUT_HOW_AM_I                                          = 11318,  -- Hmph... You're right. But how am I to get the iron?
        WHY_DON_T_YOU_JUST_COP_SOME_WEAPONS                                     = 11319,  -- Why don't you just cop some weapons from Orcs in Ghelsba? Kill two birds with one stone, that way.
        YOU_MEAN_MELT_DOWN_THE_ORCISH_WEAPONS_TO                                = 11320,  -- You mean, melt down the Orcish weapons to make new ones? Now, that's an idea. How many would you need?
        HMM_I_D_SAY_ABOUT_10_KNIVES_GIVE                                        = 11321,  -- Hmm... I'd say about 10 knives, give or take a blade.
        THEN_SPEED_IS_OUR_ALLY_QUICK_YOU_GO                                     = 11322,  -- Then speed is our ally! Quick, you go to the forest and I will report back to the captain.
        EH_I_M_A_BLACKSMITH_I_MAKE_SWORDS                                       = 11323,  -- Eh? I'm a blacksmith! I make swords, not use 'em! I'm not fighting no Orcs.
        MIND_YOUR_TONGUE_INSOLENT_SMITH_DO_YOU_NOT                              = 11324,  -- Mind your tongue, insolent smith! Do you not know who I am? I am Lord Ancolain, officer of the Royal Knights!
        REALLY_BEHAVE_YOURSELVES_WHY_DON_T_YOU_JUST                             = 11325,  -- Really, behave yourselves! Why don't you just go find an adventurer to do the job?
        THINGS_AREN_T_USUALLY_THIS_ROUGH_AROUND_HERE                            = 11326,  -- Things aren't usually this rough around here, really. Say, you look like a bit of an adventurer, yourself. How about it?
        YOU_RE_AN_ADVENTURER_RIGHT_AS_YOU_MAY                                   = 11327,  -- You're an adventurer, right? As you may have heard, we're in need of your services.
        LISTEN_TO_WHAT_HE_HAS_TO_SAY_LISTEN                                     = 11328,  -- Listen to what he has to say? Listen. Turn away.
        MY_ADVENTURERS_THESE_DAYS_TOO_BUSY_TO_LEND                              = 11329,  -- My... Adventurers these days! Too busy to lend a helping hand.
        LISTEN_CLOSE_THEY_ARE_MANY_ORCS_IN_THE                                  = 11330,  -- Listen close, they are many Orcs in the camps of Ghelsba, and some carry knives.
        MIGHT_YOU_BE_ABLE_TO_GATHER_TEN_OF                                      = 11331,  -- Might you be able to gather ten of those knives and bring them here? We've not much time.
        HOW_FARE_YOU_HAVE_YOU_GOTTEN_THE_KNIVES                                 = 11332,  -- How fare you? Have you gotten the knives?
        LOOKS_LIKE_YOU_VE_GOT_SO_FAR_BRING                                      = 11333,  -- Looks like you've got # [knife/knives] so far. Bring # more, and please hurry!
        OUR_STALWART_ADVENTURER_HAS_RETURNED_YOU_VE_BROUGHT                     = 11334,  -- Our stalwart adventurer has returned! You've brought all ten! Let's have them, then.
        THAT_S_10_ORCISH_KNIVES_PERFECT_AND_THANK                               = 11335,  -- That's 10 Orcish knives. Perfect, and thank you.
        I_SEE                                                                   = 11336,  -- I...see.
        I_M_RIGHT_IN_THE_MIDDLE_OF_SOMETHING                                    = 11337,  -- I'm right in the middle of something important. Please be quiet.
        CAN_T_YOU_SEE_I_M_BUSY_IF                                               = 11338,  -- Can't you see I'm busy? If you've some business, talk to me later.
        IT_SEEMS_THAT_OFFICER_IS_IN_A_PICKLE                                    = 11339,  -- It seems that officer is in a pickle. Maybe you could help him out, eh?
        THAT_OFFICER_WAS_SINGING_IN_PRAISE_OF_YOU                               = 11340,  -- That officer was singing in praise of you. Aye, you've the makings of a fine adventurer!
        IT_S_A_SIGN_OF_TROUBLED_TIMES_WHEN                                      = 11341,  -- It's a sign of troubled times when we're this busy. I appreciate the extra gil, but worrying for my skin isn't worth it.
        A_SMITH_IS_NOT_JUDGED_BY_HIS_STRENGTH                                   = 11342,  -- A smith is not judged by his strength, but by his skill in his art!
        THIS_IS_THE_RELIQUARY_WHERE_OUR_LATE_PAPSQUE                            = 11343,  -- This is the reliquary, where our late papsque, Muchavatte, is interred.
        WE_CONTINUE_OUR_SPIRITUAL_DISCIPLINE_HERE_SO_THAT                       = 11344,  -- We continue our spiritual discipline here, so that we may reach Paradise like His Holiness before us.
        BEHOLD_THE_CANDLES_ON_EITHER_SIDE_OF_THE                                = 11345,  -- Behold the candles on either side of the epitaph. Vigilantly their flames have burned since the departure of Papsque Muchavatte.
        THEY_ARE_PLACED_HERE_TO_LIGHT_HIS_WAY                                   = 11346,  -- They are placed here to light his way to Paradise.
        BUT_MANY_A_CANDLE_ARE_NEEDED_TO_KEEP                                    = 11347,  -- But many a candle are needed to keep his journey alight. Ever must the faithful bring % for candle-making.
        WE_HUMBLY_ASK_VISITORS_TO_DONATE_TWO_WOULD                              = 11348,  -- We humbly ask visitors to donate two %. Would you make an offering?
        ALTANA_SMILES_ON_THE_GENEROUS_ONCE_YOU_HAVE                             = 11349,  -- Altana smiles on the generous. Once you have obtained two %, carry them hither.
        SURELY_THE_LATE_PAPSQUE_FROWNS_UPON_YOU_RETURN                          = 11350,  -- Surely the late papsque frowns upon you. Return hither when you remember charity.
        MAY_PARADISE_OPEN_ITS_GATES_TO_YOU_2                                    = 11351,  -- May Paradise open its gates to you.
        I_THANK_YOU_FOR_OFFERING_TWO_THE_LATE                                   = 11352,  -- I thank you for offering two %. The late papsque would be pleased.
        IN_THANKS_FOR_YOUR_SERVICE_THE_SAN_D                                    = 11353,  -- In thanks for your service, the San d'Oria Cathedral presents you with this %. Wear it, and Altana's providence will be yours.
        I_THANK_YOU_FOR_YOUR_GENEROUS_OFFERING_BUT                              = 11354,  -- I thank you for your generous offering, but I am afraid I cannot accept this.
        I_AWAIT_YOUR_OFFERING                                                   = 11355,  -- I await your offering.
        THANK_YOU_FOR_YOUR_GENEROUS_SERVICE                                     = 11356,  -- Thank you for your generous service.
        AH_IF_IT_ISN_T_OUR_FAVORITE_ADVENTURER                                  = 11357,  -- Ah, if it isn't our favorite adventurer! The guests were overjoyed, thanks to you.
        ACTUALLY_WE_RE_IN_NEED_OF_YOUR_HELP                                     = 11358,  -- Actually, we're in need of your help again...if you have the time, that is.
        ONE_OF_OUR_GUESTS_FROM_LAST_NIGHT_HAS                                   = 11359,  -- One of our guests from last night has caught cold. We'd like to help, but we've no medicine, you see.
        THERE_IS_AN_OLD_WOMAN_NAMED_AMAURA_A                                    = 11360,  -- There is an old woman named Amaura, a brewer of salves and medicines, in Southern San d'Oria. Might you be able to fetch one from her?
        OF_COURSE_THERE_S_SOMETHING_IN_IT_FOR                                   = 11361,  -- Of course there's something in it for you, too. What do you say?
        SO_YOU_VE_DECIDED_TO_TALK_TO_AMAURA                                     = 11362,  -- So, you've decided to talk to Amaura for us?
        I_SEE_I_LL_JUST_HAVE_TO_LOOK                                            = 11363,  -- I see... I'll just have to look for someone else. Come by again if you change your mind.
        I_KNEW_YOU_WERE_THE_ONE_TO_ASK                                          = 11364,  -- I knew you were the one to ask, as always!
        AMAURA_MAKES_HER_HOME_ON_WATCHDOG_ALLEY_IF                              = 11365,  -- Amaura makes her home on Watchdog Alley. If you can't find her, ask someone along the way. I'll be waiting here!
        AH_JUST_THE_STUFF_I_LL_BUY_IT                                           = 11366,  -- Ah, just the stuff! I'll buy it from you and give it to the guest right away!
        YOU_VE_BEEN_A_GREAT_HELP_AGAIN_I                                        = 11367,  -- You've been a great help, again. I don't know how to thank you!
        HRM_MYSTERIES_WHY_IS_THIS_PART_DIFFERENT_FROM                           = 11368,  -- Hrm... Mysteries... Why is this part different from all the rest?
        A_RECEIPT_EH_I_CAN_T_READ_THIS                                          = 11369,  -- A receipt, eh? I can't read this fancy writing. Who's it for? Prince Trion, or Prince Pieuje?
        WHO_IS_IT_FOR_PRINCE_TRION_PRINCE_PIEUJE                                = 11370,  -- Who is it for? Prince Trion. Prince Pieuje.
        ID_5DY5_BJ                                                              = 11371,  -- %5DY5"Bj
        ISG_5DY5_BJ                                                             = 11372,  -- isG%5DY5"Bj
        ALL_RIGHT_I_LL_DELIVER_IT_FOR_YOU                                       = 11373,  -- All right, I'll deliver it for you. We can't let you in looking like that! Wait here.
        I_DELIVERED_THE_TO_PRINCE_TRION_YOU_RE                                  = 11374,  -- I delivered the % to Prince Trion. You're dismissed.
        I_DELIVERED_THE_TO_PRINCE_PIEUJE_YOU_RE                                 = 11375,  -- I delivered the % to Prince Pieuje. You're dismissed.
        IMBECILE_THAT_ENVELOPE_WAS_FOR_PRINCE_TRION_NOT                         = 11376,  -- Imbecile! That envelope was for Prince Trion, not Prince Pieuje! Such idiocy... Get out of here!
        IMBECILE_THAT_ENVELOPE_WAS_FOR_PRINCE_PIEUJE_NOT                        = 11377,  -- Imbecile! That envelope was for Prince Pieuje, not Prince Trion! Such idiocy... Get out of here!
        OH_AND_TELL_THAT_SHOPKEEPER_TO_SEND_SOMEONE                             = 11378,  -- Oh, and tell that shopkeeper to send someone respectable next time!
        I_VE_DELIVERED_THE_RECEIPT_GIVE_THE_PRINCE                              = 11379,  -- I've delivered the receipt. Give the prince's regards to that shopkeeper.
        NOTHING_TO_REPORT                                                       = 11380,  -- Nothing to report.
        BEHOLD_CHATEAU_D_ORAGUILLE_THE_GREATEST_FORTRESS_IN                     = 11381,  -- Behold Chateau d'Oraguille, the greatest fortress in the realm!
        YOU_STAND_BEFORE_CHATEAU_D_ORAGUILLE_IF_YOU                             = 11382,  -- You stand before Chateau d'Oraguille. If you've no business here, begone!
        HEY_WHO_SAID_YOU_COULD_GO_IN_GET                                        = 11383,  -- Hey! Who said you could go in? Get back here, scum!
        PROCEED                                                                 = 11384,  -- Proceed!
        THIS_IS_VICTORY_ARCH_BEYOND_LIES_SOUTHERN_SAN                           = 11385,  -- This is Victory Arch. Beyond lies Southern San d'Oria.
        YOU_STAND_BEFORE_VICTORY_ARCH_SOUTHERN_SAN_D                            = 11386,  -- You stand before Victory Arch. Southern San d'Oria is on the other side.
        THIS_GATE_LEADS_TO_PORT_SAN_D_ORIA                                      = 11387,  -- This gate leads to Port San d'Oria.
        THIS_IS_RANPERRE_GATE_FIENDS_LURK_IN_THE                                = 11388,  -- This is Ranperre Gate. Fiends lurk in the lands beyond, so take caution!
        BLESSED_ARE_THOSE_WHO_CHERISH_ALTANA_AND_HEED                           = 11389,  -- Blessed are those who cherish Altana and heed the word of the papsque. To them the Gates of Paradise will open.
        WE_RE_HERE_TO_SEE_THE_PAPSQUE_ADDRESS                                   = 11390,  -- We're here to see the papsque address the faithful. He sometimes stands at the cathedral balcony beneath the steeple.
        HMM_HIS_HOLINESS_SHOULD_APPEAR_SOON                                     = 11391,  -- Hmm... His Holiness should appear soon.
        I_SEE_HIM_THE_PAPSQUE                                                   = 11392,  -- I see him! The papsque!
        YES_THERE_HE_IS                                                         = 11393,  -- Yes, there he is!
        BELOVED_SAN_D_ORIA_ALTANA_WATCHES_OVER_US                               = 11394,  -- Beloved San d'Oria, Altana watches over us, always.
        SHE_IS_THE_ALLY_OF_THE_WEAK_SHE                                         = 11395,  -- She is the ally of the weak. She feeds the hungry and clothes the needy.
        SHE_HAS_GIVEN_US_THE_PATH_TO_ETERNAL                                    = 11396,  -- She has given us the path to eternal Paradise. By this trial shall she judge us all.
        MAY_PARADISE_OPEN_ITS_GATES_TO_ALL_HER                                  = 11397,  -- May Paradise open its gates to all her children!
        HIS_WORDS_RESOUND_IN_MY_HEART_LONG_AFTER                                = 11398,  -- His words resound in my heart, long after they are spoken.
        EVERY_TIME_I_SEE_THE_PAPSQUE_I_FEEL                                     = 11399,  -- Every time I see the papsque, I feel as though I'm one step closer to Paradise!
        EVERYONE_SHOULD_SEEK_BLESSING_FROM_THE_PAPSQUE_HIMSELF                  = 11400,  -- Everyone should seek blessing from the papsque himself!
        WELCOME_TO_THE_CONSULATE_OF_JEUNO_I_AM                                  = 11401,  -- Welcome to the Consulate of Jeuno. I am Galahad, Consul to San d'Oria.
        MAY_I_ASSIST_YOU                                                        = 11402,  -- May I assist you?
        IF_YOU_HAVE_BUSINESS_WITH_CONSUL_GALAHAD_YOU                            = 11403,  -- If you have business with Consul Galahad, you'll find him inside.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_CONSULATE_OF_JEUNO                                       = 11404,  -- Welcome to the Consulate of Jeuno.
        HELLO_THERE_I_M_THE_CONSUL_FROM_BASTOK                                  = 11405,  -- Hello there. I'm the consul from Bastok. Name's Helaku.
        I_M_CONSUL_HELAKU_DIDN_T_YOU_BRING                                      = 11406,  -- I'm Consul Helaku. Didn't you bring %? Oh well, just take a look around then. Might as well enjoy the place while you're here.
        PARDON_ME_BUT_WE_RE_IN_THE_MIDDLE                                       = 11407,  -- Pardon me, but we're in the middle of a very important discussion here.
        YOU_RE_HERE_WITH_BUSINESS_FROM_THE_ADMINISTRATION                       = 11408,  -- You're here with business from the administration, correct? I believe you should talk to Consul Helaku.
        YOU_RE_HERE_WITH_BUSINESS_FROM_THE_ADMINISTRATION_2                     = 11409,  -- You're here with business from the administration, correct? You should probably talk to Consul Helaku.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_CONSULATE_OF_BASTOK                                      = 11410,  -- Welcome to the Consulate of Bastok.
        A_SAN_D_ORIAN_HUH_THIS_IS_THE                                           = 11411,  -- A San d'Orian, huh? This is the Consulate of Bastok. We're here to serve travelers from Bastok.
        A_WINDURSTIAN_HUH_THIS_IS_THE_CONSULATE_OF                              = 11412,  -- A Windurstian, huh? This is the Consulate of Bastok. The Consulate of Windurst is right outside.
        CONSUL_HELAKU_GO_IN                                                     = 11413,  -- Consul Helaku? Go in.
        REALLY_YOU_DON_T_SAY_THANK_YOU                                          = 11414,  -- Really? You don't say... Thank you.
        YOU_VE_COME_ALL_THE_WAY_FROM_BASTOK                                     = 11415,  -- You've come all the way from Bastok, have you? I'm Lion, a traveling adventurer, you might say.
        YOU_VE_COME_ALL_THE_WAY_FROM_WINDURST                                   = 11416,  -- You've come all the way from Windurst, have you? I'm Lion, a traveling adventurer, you might say.
        HAVE_YOU_HEARD_THE_ORCS_HAVE_A_NEW                                      = 11417,  -- Have you heard? The Orcs have a new forward base in Ghelsba, to the northwest. Now their greedy eyes are turned towards this land!
        ORCS_ARE_CRUEL_AND_VIOLENT_THEY_ATTACK_WAYFARERS                        = 11418,  -- Orcs are cruel and violent. They attack wayfarers on the road, and steal children, all to inspire terror in the San d'Orian people.
        BUT_THERE_S_ONE_THING_THAT_JUST_DOESN                                   = 11419,  -- But, there's one thing that just doesn't make sense.
        ORCS_NEVER_WERE_KNOWN_FOR_THEIR_CRAFT_BUT                               = 11420,  -- Orcs never were known for their craft, but they carry even better armor and weapons lately.
        I_SUSPECT_THERE_S_SOMEONE_BEHIND_THE_ORCS                               = 11421,  -- I suspect there's someone behind the Orcs, pulling the strings, if you get me.
        SOMEONE_HAS_TO_FIGURE_OUT_THEIR_PLANS_AND                               = 11422,  -- Someone has to figure out their plans and take action, before this country falls to an Orcish invasion!
        PEOPLE_WHISPER_IN_THE_STREETS_OF_TROUBLE_IN                             = 11423,  -- People whisper in the streets of trouble in the royal house. They should focus on what's outside their walls first, if you ask me.
        WELL_I_DON_T_EXPECT_THINGS_WILL_BE                                      = 11424,  -- Well, I don't expect things will be getting any easier around here for a while yet, but you take care, all the same.
        YOU_MUST_BE_TIRED_FROM_YOUR_TRIP_BUT                                    = 11425,  -- You must be tired from your trip. But first, let me get you up to speed on the situation here in San d'Oria.
        NORTHWEST_OF_THE_CITY_IS_AN_ORC_VILLAGE                                 = 11426,  -- Northwest of the city is an Orc village. They call it Ghelsba Outpost.
        OUR_REPORTS_TELL_US_THAT_THE_ORCS_ARE                                   = 11427,  -- Our reports tell us that the Orcs are using Ghelsba as a forward base for an upcoming invasion of San d'Oria, but there's a few things that just don't fit.
        WE_ALL_KNOW_THAT_ORCS_ARE_BEASTMEN_RIGHT                                = 11428,  -- We all know that Orcs are beastmen, right? To say they're low on brains would be an understatement.
        WHICH_IS_WHY_I_WONDER_HOW_THEY_CAME                                     = 11429,  -- Which is why I wonder how they came by the high-quality armor and weapons they've been using. Not to mention the ranged weapons and devices!
        WE_SUSPECT_THERE_S_SOMEONE_BEHIND_THE_BEASTMEN                          = 11430,  -- We suspect there's someone behind the beastmen calling the shots, but we've no idea who.
        I_WISH_I_COULD_SEND_YOU_TO_GHELSBA                                      = 11431,  -- I wish I could send you to Ghelsba immediately, but in this region official missions require San d'Orian approval.
        WHAT_I_WANT_YOU_TO_DO_IS_GO                                             = 11432,  -- What I want you to do is go to Chateau d'Oraguille and speak to Monarlais Halver. He'll issue you a formal mission order.
        LEAVE_THIS_BUILDING_AND_YOU_LL_SEE_A                                    = 11433,  -- Leave this building, and you'll see a great fortress to the right. That's Chateau d'Oraguille. And be polite; San d'Orians can be quite touchy.
        LOOKS_LIKE_LORD_HALVER_GAVE_YOU_YOUR_ORDERS                             = 11434,  -- Looks like Lord Halver gave you your orders. Good luck, and be careful out there.
        IT_IS_GOOD_TO_SEE_YOU_ARE_WELL                                          = 11435,  -- It is good to see you are well! Lord Helaku will be pleased to see you again.
        WELCOME_BACK_YOU_DIDN_T_GET_HURT_DID                                    = 11436,  -- Welcome back! You didn't get hurt, did you?
        MONARLAIS_HALVER_TELLS_ME_YOU_WENT_TO_DEFEAT                            = 11437,  -- Monarlais Halver tells me you went to defeat Warchief Vatgit, eh?
        A_LOT_OF_ADVENTURERS_MAKE_THEIR_WAY_INTO                                = 11438,  -- A lot of adventurers make their way into the Ghelsba Outpost, but most turn around once they get up to the higher encampment.
        WELL_YOU_VE_DONE_A_GREAT_JOB_AS                                         = 11439,  -- Well, you've done a great job. As consul, I'm honored to congratulate you on a mission well done.
        I_LL_BE_SURE_SAN_D_ORIA_MAKES                                           = 11440,  -- I'll be sure San d'Oria makes you a certified adventurer, %.
        NOW_THAT_THAT_S_SETTLED_YOUR_NEXT_GOAL                                  = 11441,  -- Now that that's settled, your next goal is Windurst! It's a wild world out there, so keep your wits about you.
        WHAT_S_THIS_HERE_TAKE_IT_BACK                                           = 11442,  -- What's this? Here, take it back.
        JUST_THE_THING_I_COUNT_NO_MORE_NO                                       = 11443,  -- Just the thing! I count #; no more, no less. Good job, %.
        NEXT_STOP_WINDURST_EH_GOOD_LUCK_AND_WATCH                               = 11444,  -- Next stop: Windurst, eh? Good luck, and watch yourself out there!
        AH_IS_IT_I_HEARD_GOOD_THINGS_ABOUT                                      = 11445,  -- Ah, %, is it? I heard good things about you from Consul Melek in Windurst.
        SAN_D_ORIA_IS_LOCKED_IN_BATTLE_WITH                                     = 11446,  -- San d'Oria is locked in battle with the Orcish horde. It's tough on the townsfolk. They can't even go outside without fearing for their lives these days.
        THE_ROYAL_HOUSE_IS_TRYING_TO_SUPPRESS_THE                               = 11447,  -- The royal house is trying to suppress the beastmen. But with so much intrigue in the royal family, they can't take decisive action!
        BUT_I_SHOULDN_T_KEEP_YOU_HERE_TOO                                       = 11448,  -- But I shouldn't keep you here too long. I don't know the details of your special assignment, myself.
        YOU_ARE_TO_HEAD_TO_CHATEAU_D_ORAGUILLE                                  = 11449,  -- You are to head to Chateau d'Oraguille and speak to the San d'Orian monarlais Lord Halver. He'll tell you all you need to know.
        YOU_VE_DONE_IT_AGAIN_YOU_MAKE_ME                                        = 11450,  -- You've done it again! You make me proud!
        YOU_VE_BEEN_OFFICIALLY_CERTIFIED_BY_THE_KING                            = 11451,  -- You've been officially certified by the King of San d'Oria. Now all there's to do is to go home and get your %, and you'll be an official adventurer.
        MAKE_HASTE_BACK_TO_THE_HOMELAND_AND_GO                                  = 11452,  -- Make haste back to the homeland and go to see Naji by the President's Office. He'll be waiting for you.
        ALSO_I_D_BE_MUCH_OBLIGED_IF_YOU                                         = 11453,  -- Also, I'd be much obliged if you could bring this report back when you go. Don't forget to give it to him, now.
        YOU_D_BEST_GET_BACK_TO_THE_HOMELAND                                     = 11454,  -- You'd best get back to the homeland. Naji is probably wondering where you are by now.
        WELL_IF_IT_ISN_T_YOU_LOOK_WELL                                          = 11455,  -- Well, if it isn't %! You look well! Stay as long as you like. You deserve a rest, my friend.
        GREETINGS_I_AM_CONSUL_KASARORO_AT_YOUR_SERVICE                          = 11456,  -- Greetings! I am Consul Kasaroro, at your service. How may I help you?
        I_AM_CONSUL_KASARORO_WHAT_YOU_DON_T                                     = 11457,  -- I am Consul Kasaroro. What? You don't have %? You'll have to bring one if you've business with me!
        WELCOME_TO_THE_CONSULATE_OF_WINDURST                                    = 11458,  -- Welcome to the Consulate of Windurst!
        IF_IT_S_THE_CONSUL_YOU_RE_A                                             = 11459,  -- If it's the consul you're a-seeking, she's inside!
        A_SAN_D_ORIAN_ARE_YOU_THIS_IS                                           = 11460,  -- A San d'Orian, are you? This is the Consulate of Windurst. We provide all sorts of aid to our countrymen here.
        A_BASTOKER_ARE_YOU_THIS_IS_THE_CONSULATE                                = 11461,  -- A Bastoker, are you? This is the Consulate of Windurst. If you're looking for your consulate, it's out the door and across the way.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_CONSULATE_OF_WINDURST_CONSUL_KASARORO                    = 11462,  -- Welcome to the Consulate of Windurst. Consul Kasaroro is inside, if you're looking forrr her.
        YOU_VE_COME_ON_ORDERS_FROM_THE_HOMELAND                                 = 11463,  -- You've come on orders from the homeland, have you? You should speak with Consul Kasaroro.
        GREETINGS_I_AM_CONSUL_KASARORO_LET_ME_TELL                              = 11464,  -- Greetings, %! I am Consul Kasaroro. Let me tell you about current events here in the Kingdom of San d'Oria.
        BEASTMEN_KNOWN_AS_ORCS_STEADILY_GROW_IN_NUMBER                          = 11465,  -- Beastmen known as Orcs steadily grow in number outside San d'Oria.
        THEY_HAVE_SET_UP_A_FORWARD_BASE_IN                                      = 11466,  -- They have set up a forward base in Ghelsba, northwest of San d'Oria. From here, they plan to launch an invasion!
        ORCS_LOVE_BATTLE_WATTLE_BUT_THEY_AREN_T                                 = 11467,  -- Orcs love battle-wattle, but they aren't the brightest bunch. There's just one thing...
        IT_SEEMS_THEIR_ARMOR_AND_WEAPONS_HAVE_BEEN                              = 11468,  -- It seems their armor and weapons have been improving by the day-way! Now they're using traps and bows, too!
        I_AND_A_FEW_OTHERS_THINK_THAT_THERE                                     = 11469,  -- I, and a few others, think that there's somebody behind these Orcs, supplying them with the goods, and calling the shots. But there's not enough to go on right now.
        IF_IT_WERE_UP_TO_ME_I_D                                                 = 11470,  -- If it were up to me, I'd send you to Ghelsba pronto! But this is San d'Oria, and missions are their jurisdiction.
        SO_FIRST_YOU_SHOULD_TALK_TO_MONARLAIS_HALVER                            = 11471,  -- So, first you should talk to Monarlais Halver in Chateau d'Oraguille. He'll give you official orders.
        STEP_RIGHT_OUTSIDE_AND_YOU_LL_SEE_A                                     = 11472,  -- Step right outside, and you'll see a big castle on the left. That's Chateau d'Oraguille. They're a little touchy in there, so mind your manners!
        SO_YOU_VE_GOTTEN_AN_OFFER_WOFFER_FROM                                   = 11473,  -- So you've gotten an offer-woffer from Monarlais Halver? Excellent! Take care out there.
        WELCOME_BACK_I_TRUST_YOU_WEREN_T_HURTARU                                = 11474,  -- Welcome back. I trust you weren't hurtaru?
        I_HEARD_FROM_THE_MONARLAIS_THAT_YOU_WENT                                = 11475,  -- I heard from the monarlais that you went to fight-wight the great Warchief Vatgit!
        A_GREAT_MANY_ADVENTURERS_SEE_GHELSBA_OUTPOST_ON                         = 11476,  -- A great many adventurers see Ghelsba Outpost on missions, but most turn back at the highland encampmentaru!
        YOU_VE_DONE_SWELLSY_WELLSY_I_M_PROUD                                    = 11477,  -- You've done swellsy-wellsy! I'm proud to be your consul.
        I_LL_FORMALLY_REQUEST_THE_SAN_D_ORIAN                                   = 11478,  -- I'll formally request the San d'Orian court to certify you, %, as an official adventurer.
        NOW_ALL_YOU_HAVE_TO_DO_IS_GET                                           = 11479,  -- Now all you have to do is get recognition from Bastok. Keep your wits about you, and you'll be finey-shiney!
        THIS_ISN_T_WHAT_I_ASKED_FOR_TAKE                                        = 11480,  -- This isn't what I asked for. Take it backeddy-wackeddy!
        AH_THANK_YOU_VERY_MUCH_YOUR_MISSION_HERE                                = 11481,  -- Ah! #! Thank you very much. Your mission here is completaru!
        NOW_YOU_JUST_HAVE_TO_COMPLETE_A_MISSION                                 = 11482,  -- Now you just have to complete a mission for Bastok! It's a dangerous world out there, so take care-beware!
        WHY_IT_S_I_HEARD_ABOUT_YOUR_SUCCESS                                     = 11483,  -- Why, it's %! I heard about your success from Consul Patt-Pott in Bastok. Sounds like you've done a bang-up job!
        THAT_PATT_POTT_TALKS_A_MALM_A_MINUTE                                    = 11484,  -- That Patt-Pott talks a malm-a-minute, so it was hard to make out what he was saying at firstaru...
        BUT_THAT_S_NEITHER_HERE_NOR_THERE_WHERE                                 = 11485,  -- But that's neither here nor there-where! The war goes on here in San d'Oria, and the civilians are trying to cope.
        I_KNOW_THE_KINGDOM_WANTS_TO_SETTLE_THINGS                               = 11486,  -- I know the Kingdom wants to settle things quickly, but with all the hubbub going on in the royal family, they can't focus on the war!
        THERE_S_A_SPECIAL_MISSION_WAITING_FOR_YOU                               = 11487,  -- There's a special mission waiting for you. Even I haven't heard what it's all aboutaru!
        YOU_LL_HAVE_TO_HEAD_TO_CHATEAU_D                                        = 11488,  -- You'll have to head to Chateau d'Oraguille and ask Monarlais Halver. He'll fill you in, he will!
        I_VE_HEARD_OF_WHAT_YOU_DID_AND                                          = 11489,  -- I've heard of what you did, and I have to say I'm impressed! You make me proud to be a Windurstian!
        I_HEAR_YOU_VE_BEEN_OFFICIALLY_RECOGNIZED_BY                             = 11490,  -- I hear you've been officially recognized by San d'Oria, too. The next time you return to the homeland, pick up your %.
        ALSO_WHEN_YOU_DO_GO_BACK_COULD_YOU                                      = 11491,  -- Also, when you do go back, could you hand this report to Lady Kupipi, at the Heavens Tower? Don't forgetaru!
        NOW_BACK_HOME_YOU_GO_I_M_SURE                                           = 11492,  -- Now, back home you go! I'm sure Lady Kupipi eagerly awaits your return.
        RIGHT_YOU_SEEM_WELL_SWELL_FEEL_FREE_TO                                  = 11493,  -- %, right? You seem well-swell! Feel free to hang around as long as you like!
        ALL_RIGHT_ONCE_MORE                                                     = 11494,  -- All right, once more!
        ONE                                                                     = 11495,  -- One!
        TWO                                                                     = 11496,  -- Two!
        STOP                                                                    = 11497,  -- Stop!
        WHAT_S_THE_MEANING_OF_THIS_DON_T                                        = 11498,  -- What's the meaning of this? Don't interrupt!
        WELCOME_WE_HAVE_ALL_KINDS_OF_FURNISHINGS_HERE                           = 11499,  -- Welcome. We have all kinds of furnishings here!
        HOW_CAN_I_HELP_YOU                                                      = 11500,  -- How can I help you?
        A_PICKPOCKET_YOU_SAY_COME_TO_THINK_OF                                   = 11501,  -- A pickpocket, you say? Come to think of it, I did see a scoundrel skulking about...
        HMM_I_VE_NO_IDEA_WHAT_YOU_RE                                            = 11502,  -- Hmm... I've no idea what you're talking about.
        A_PICKPOCKET_NO_CAN_T_SAY_I_VE                                          = 11503,  -- A pickpocket? No, can't say I've seen anyone like that. I'll keep an eye out, though.
        A_PICKPOCKET_I_VE_GOT_BIGGER_FISH_TO                                    = 11504,  -- A pickpocket? I've got bigger fish to fry! Ask someone else.
        A_PICKPOCKET_YOU_SAY_HMM_COME_TO_THINK                                  = 11505,  -- A pickpocket, you say? Hmm... Come to think of it, I did spot a strange woman running across the bridge over there a bit ago.
        SHE_RAN_TOWARD_THAT_GATE_WHICH_WOULD_MEAN                               = 11506,  -- She ran toward that gate, which would mean she could be at the Parade Grounds by now.
        A_PICKPOCKET_HEY_I_WONDER_IF_YOU_MEAN                                   = 11507,  -- A pickpocket? Hey, I wonder if you mean that lady running helter-skelter over there just now...
        A_PICKPOCKET_I_DID_JUST_SEE_AN_UNDIGNIFIED                              = 11508,  -- A pickpocket? I did just see an undignified sort of woman just now. She was running toward Ranperre Gate.
        THIS_PART_OF_TOWN_IS_SO_LIVELY_I                                        = 11509,  -- This part of town is so lively, I like watching everybody just go about their business.
        A_PICKPOCKET                                                            = 11510,  -- A pickpocket?
        WELL_I_DID_SEE_A_STRANGER_SHE_RAN                                       = 11511,  -- Well, I did see a stranger. She ran for the gate over there just now.
        A_PICKPOCKET_MAYBE_IT_WAS_THAT_FOUL_MOUTHED                             = 11512,  -- A pickpocket? Maybe it was that foul-mouthed woman just now. She called me a spoony bard! Unthinkable!
        GOOD_DAY_I_AM_ULYCILLE_HAVE_YOU_AN                                      = 11513,  -- Good day. I am Ulycille. Have you an interest in woodworking?
        SAN_D_ORIAN_WOODWORKERS_ARE_BLESSED_WITH_AN                             = 11514,  -- San d'Orian woodworkers are blessed with an abundance of raw material, for our kingdom is surrounded by wooded hills.
        SHOULD_YOU_LOOK_TO_REFINE_YOUR_SKILL_IN                                 = 11515,  -- Should you look to refine your skill in woodworking, heed this counsel: San d'Oria is the perfect place to start!
        AN_ADVENTURER_ARE_YOU_THIS_IS_ONE_OF                                    = 11516,  -- An adventurer, are you? This is one of the finest workshops in the land. Of course, much depends on you.
        SHOULD_YOU_WISH_TO_REFINE_YOUR_SKILL_CRAFT                              = 11517,  -- Should you wish to refine your skill, craft the same thing over and over. Work hard, and you may become known among us.
        SAY_HAVE_YOU_HEARD                                                      = 11518,  -- Say, have you heard?
        ABOUT_THE_PRINCES_WHO_HAS_NOT_THINGS_ARE                                = 11519,  -- About the princes? Who has not? Things are getting worse, I hear!
        YES_BUT_I_TRUST_PRINCE_TRION_MORE_THAN                                  = 11520,  -- Yes, but I trust Prince Trion more than Prince Pieuje. He's the elder, and stronger, of the two.
        OH_HE_S_ALL_BRAWN_AND_NO_BRAINS                                         = 11521,  -- Oh, he's all brawn and no brains, unfit to decide the fate of our kingdom. I would follow Prince Pieuje, personally.
        IS_IT_JUST_ME_OR_ARE_THERE_MORE                                         = 11522,  -- Is it just me, or are there more strangers in town these days? Whatever could it mean?
        WHAT_HAVE_YOU_NOT_HEARD_THEY_ARE_RECRUITING                             = 11523,  -- What, have you not heard? They are recruiting adventurers in droves!
        I_HEAR_THEY_RE_TAKING_ANY_WHO_WILL                                      = 11524,  -- I hear they're taking any who will come--foreigners, even!
        WELL_GUESS_WHAT_HAPPENED_TO_ME_I_WAS                                    = 11525,  -- Well, guess what happened to me. I was tidying the house yesterday, when a strange man walked in. He then ran out the veranda without even saying hello!
        SHAME_ON_THOSE_ADVENTURERS_AT_LEAST_THEY_COULD                          = 11526,  -- Shame on those adventurers! At least they could knock before barging into our homes.
        ARE_YOU_A_NEW_RECRUIT_HELLO_I_AM                                        = 11527,  -- Are you a new recruit? Hello, I am Matildie.
        YOU_SEEM_NICE_MUCH_NICER_THAN_THE_OTHER                                 = 11528,  -- You seem nice--much nicer than the other adventurers. Remember, ask for help if you lose your way!
        WHY_DON_T_I_GIVE_YOU_A_LITTLE                                           = 11529,  -- Why don't I give you a little money for your % there, just to get you started. Spend it wisely!
        SHOULD_YOU_LOSE_YOUR_WAY_JUST_CHECK_YOUR                                = 11530,  -- Should you lose your way, just check your Map from the main menu.
        FAREWELL_AND_GOOD_LUCK_TO_YOU                                           = 11531,  -- Farewell, and good luck to you!
        GOODBYE                                                                 = 11532,  -- Goodbye!
        THESE_SLUICE_GATES_DIVIDE_NORTHERN_SAN_D_ORIA                           = 11533,  -- These sluice gates divide Northern San d'Oria into two parts: the Parade Grounds, and Laborman's Way.
        LABORMAN_S_WAY_IS_MUCH_LOWER_THAN_THE                                   = 11534,  -- Laborman's Way is much lower than the rest of the city. So to prevent flooding, we use these sluice gates to adjust the water for the entire district!
        WAIT_YOU_RE_AN_ADVENTURER_AREN_T_YOU                                    = 11535,  -- Wait, you're an adventurer, aren't you? I have a request, if you've the time...
        DON_T_TELL_ANYONE_BUT_SOMEONE_SENT_ME                                   = 11536,  -- Don't tell anyone, but someone sent me a letter saying they poisoned the water here! We're looking into the veracity of that claim now.
        IN_THE_MEANTIME_WE_MUST_PREPARE_A_NEUTRALIZER                           = 11537,  -- In the meantime, we must prepare a neutralizer to eliminate the poison. Might you be willing to obtain one?
        GO_FETCH_THE_NEUTRALIZER_LET_S_DO_IT                                    = 11538,  -- Go fetch the neutralizer? Let's do it. Not right now.
        THAT_IS_GOOD_NEWS_INDEED_NOW_ALL_WE                                     = 11539,  -- That is good news, indeed! Now, all we need is someone versed in the ways of poison, but they're a hard lot to find...
        OH_WE_CAN_T_JUST_LET_INNOCENT_PEOPLE                                    = 11540,  -- Oh, we can't just let innocent people die from poisoned water now, can we?
        IT_S_NO_EASY_TASK_FINDING_A_NEUTRALIZER                                 = 11541,  -- It's no easy task, finding a neutralizer, is it? Few are skilled in the arts of poison, though that's a good thing, I suppose.
        YOU_VE_GOT_THE_NEUTRALIZER_BUT_THE_THING                                = 11542,  -- You've got the neutralizer! But, the thing is...it turns out it was all just a hoax. But we'll reward you anyway.
        THAT_S_FUNNY_I_COULD_HAVE_SWORN_SHE                                     = 11543,  -- That's funny. I could have sworn she asked me to meet her here...
        HE_S_LATE_I_DO_HOPE_HE_HASN                                             = 11544,  -- He's late! I do hope he hasn't forgotten.
        STARS_ARE_MORE_BEAUTIFUL_UP_CLOSE_DON_T                                 = 11545,  -- Stars are more beautiful up close. Don't you agree?
        AT_NIGHT_THE_STARRY_SKY_HERE_IS_A                                       = 11546,  -- At night, the starry sky here is a sight to behold! If it weren't for all those chimneys, it'd be a finer sight still!
        HELLO                                                                   = 11547,  -- Hello.
        AH_GOOD_DAY_I_AM_MORJEAN_A_RESEARCHER                                   = 11548,  -- Ah, good day. I am Morjean, a researcher here studying the rich past of our kingdom.
        ID_11549                                                                = 11549,  -- %?
        I_M_NOT_ENTIRELY_CERTAIN_BUT_PERHAPS_I                                  = 11550,  -- I'm not entirely certain, but perhaps I have heard a story about this thing you seek.
        IN_ORDER_TO_GET_YOUR_HANDS_MUST_NOT                                     = 11551,  -- In order to get %, your hands must not be dry... I'm sure that's what I read. But it was so many years ago...
        THAT_S_ALL_I_KNOW_I_DO_HOPE                                             = 11552,  -- That's all I know... I do hope it will be of some use to you.
        DID_YOU_FIND_THE_DEW_NO_NO_THERE                                        = 11553,  -- Did you find the dew? No, no, there's no need to thank me. It is my job to delve into the mysteries of this land, one at a time.
        IT_S_LOCKED                                                             = 11554,  -- It's locked.
        YOU_CANNOT_REACH_THE_DOORKNOB                                           = 11555,  -- You cannot reach the doorknob.
        YOU_CAN_T_POSSIBLY_CARRY_ANY_MORE_GIL                                   = 11556,  -- You can't possibly carry any more gil.
        YOUR_FLYER_IS_REFUSED                                                   = 11557,  -- Your flyer is refused.
