        I_UNDERSTAND_YOUR_WORDS_YOUR_HOLINESS_BUT_I                             = 12703,  -- I understand your words, Your Holiness, but I feel it is my duty to first report these new findings to my father.
        YOUR_HOLINESS_2                                                         = 12704,  -- Your Holiness.
        WILL_YOU_JOURNEY_INTO_THE_BOSTAUNIEUX_OUBLIETTE_AND                     = 12705,  -- %, will you journey into the Bostaunieux Oubliette and investigate the findings?
        ON_THE_OUTSIDE_THE_PRINCE_MAY_DENY_IT                                   = 12706,  -- On the outside, the prince may deny it, but on the inside, he is counting on your success in this mission.
        ACCORDING_TO_THE_NEWLY_DECIPHERED_PARCHMENT_SCIENTISTS_HID              = 12707,  -- According to the newly deciphered parchment, scientists hid something down in the Bostaunieux Oubliette during the time of war. I want you to journey down there and find that something.
        I_SEE_SO_YOU_DID_NOT_FIND_LIGHTBRINGER                                  = 12708,  -- I see... So you did not find Lightbringer. But what you have found is truly a possession of the lost Dragon King.
        YOUR_HOLINESS_THE_ROYAL_KNIGHTS_SENT_TO_INVESTIGATE                     = 12709,  -- Your Holiness, the Royal Knights sent to investigate the Bostaunieux Oubliette have returned. Their search turned up nothing.
        WHAT_IS_THAT                                                            = 12710,  -- What is that!?
        PRINCE_PIEUJE_RETRIEVED_THIS_STONE_TABLET_FROM_DEEP                     = 12711,  -- Prince Pieuje, % retrieved this stone tablet from deep within the oubliette.
        WHEN_THE_GREAT_KING_RANPERRE_BROUGHT_THE_CHAOS                          = 12712,  -- When the great King Ranperre brought the chaos in San d'Oria under control, it is said that his admonition was carved in stone.
        THIS_MAY_BE_THAT_VERY_TABLET_MY_PRINCE                                  = 12713,  -- This may be that very tablet, my prince.
        I_WAS_CORRECT_IN_ASSUMING_THAT_THE_ROYAL                                = 12714,  -- I was correct in assuming that the Royal Knights would not be suited for a task such as this--one that requires perseverance.
        HOWEVER_WE_CANNOT_BE_SURE_THAT_THIS_TABLET                              = 12715,  -- However, we cannot be sure that this tablet is King Ranperre's...
        ABSOLUTELY_THERE_IS_STILL_MUCH_DECIPHERING_THAT_MUST                    = 12716,  -- Absolutely. There is still much deciphering that must be carried out by our scholars. It will require much more time.
        HOWEVER_I_PROMISE_YOU_THAT_I_WILL_MAKE                                  = 12717,  -- However, I promise you that I will make this task our top priority.
        AS_FOR_THE_REPORT_ON_OUR_FINDING_OF                                     = 12718,  -- As for the report on our finding of the tablet, I shall take the matter up with the king myself.
        AND_AS_FOR_YOU_ONCE_THE_DECIPHERING_HAS                                 = 12719,  -- And as for you, %. Once the deciphering has been completed, we may have another task for you.
        GOOD_DAY                                                                = 12720,  -- Good day.
        YOU_SAY_YOU_WERE_UNDER_ORDERS_FROM_THE                                  = 12721,  -- You say you were under orders from the papsque? I am sorry for all the trouble he may have caused you.
        WHEN_IT_COMES_TO_THE_SUBJECT_OF_LIGHTBRINGER                            = 12722,  -- When it comes to the subject of Lightbringer, the papsque becomes a different man...
        I_HEREBY_CONCLUDE_THE_COMING_OF_AGE_CEREMONY                            = 12723,  -- I hereby conclude the coming-of-age ceremony of Claidie I d'Oraguille.
        SO_THE_BABY_PRINCESS_HAS_FINALLY_BECOME_A                               = 12724,  -- So the baby princess has finally become a lady... Did you know that it is custom at the coming-of-age ceremony for the dark d'Oraguille secrets to be revealed?
        I_M_SURE_YOU_HAVE_ALREADY_HEARD_THAT                                    = 12725,  -- I'm sure you have already heard that during the Great War, the d'Oraguille family betrayed my father, Altedour, and dragged Tavnazia into ruin.
        SILENCE_INFIDEL                                                         = 12726,  -- Silence, infidel!
        WHO_ARE                                                                 = 12727,  -- Who are...
        WHERE_DID_THIS_VAGRANT_COME_FROM                                        = 12728,  -- Where did this vagrant come from!?
        NO_I_DO_NOT_EXPECT_YOU_TO_KNOW                                          = 12729,  -- No, I do not expect you to know who I am. This is the first time I have been to this cathedral.
        WAIT_YOU_LOOK_FAMILIAR_BUT_YOU_COULDN_T                                 = 12730,  -- Wait, you look familiar. But you couldn't be...
        BUT_I_AM_MY_NAME_IS_ROCHEFOGNE_I                                        = 12731,  -- But I am. My name is Rochefogne I Tavnazia. Son of Altedour, and sole surviving heir to the Tavnazian throne.
        MY_MOTHER_S_BROTHER                                                     = 12732,  -- My mother's...brother!?
        ROCHEFOGNE_YOU_WERE_SLAIN_IN_THE_GREAT_WAR                              = 12733,  -- Rochefogne!? You were slain in the Great War!
        YOU_DOUBT_YOUR_OWN_EYES_PITIFUL_D_ORAGUILLE                             = 12734,  -- You doubt your own eyes? Pitiful d'Oraguille. That will be the downfall of you all.
        KNOW_THIS_D_ORAGUILLES_I_WILL_FIND_LIGHTBRINGER                         = 12735,  -- Know this, d'Oraguilles: I will find Lightbringer. It is the destiny that drives me.
        AFTER_HIM                                                               = 12736,  -- After him!
        STOP_SCOUNDREL                                                          = 12737,  -- Stop, scoundrel!
        WAIT                                                                    = 12738,  -- Wait!
        THAT_ROCHEFOGNE_IS_A_POISON_IN_OUR_FAIR                                 = 12739,  -- That Rochefogne is a poison in our fair country. Dispatch the knights and have them comb the countryside--no, all of Vana'diel--for him!
        BUT_HOW_COULD_IT_BE_AND_WHAT_COULD                                      = 12740,  -- But how could it be...and what could he want with the holy sword...?
        GOOD_DAY_TAKE_A_LOOK_AT_MY_SELECTION                                    = 12741,  -- Good day! Take a look at my selection from Li'Telor!
        SPECIALTY_GOODS_FROM_VOLLBOW_SPECIALTY_GOODS_FROM_VOLLBOW               = 12742,  -- Specialty goods from Vollbow! Specialty goods from Vollbow!
        SIGH_WHY_MUST_ALL_CRAFTSMEN_BE_SO_UPTIGHT                               = 12743,  -- <Sigh> Why must all craftsmen be so uptight?
        I_WISH_TO_HAVE_A_BREASTPLATE_REPAIRED_AT                                = 12744,  -- I wish to have a breastplate repaired at the Blacksmiths' Guild, but the people who work there are so difficult to approach... Would you mind coming with me?
        GO_ALONG_SURE_I_LL_GO_WITH_YOU                                          = 12745,  -- Go along? Sure, I'll go with you. I don't have time to hold your hand.
        YOU_LL_COME_THANK_YOU_I_GET_SO                                          = 12746,  -- You'll come? Thank you. I get so nervous sometimes!
        EXCUSE_ME_I_WOULD_LIKE_TO_HAVE_THIS                                     = 12747,  -- Excuse me... I would like to have this repaired. It's a keepsake from my father, but it's become a little weathered.
        LET_S_TAKE_A_LOOK_AH_THIS_IS                                            = 12748,  -- Let's take a look... Ah, this is far too old to repair. You'd be better off buying a new one. We have a range of goods here, so why don't you go pick something out.
