        HAVE_YOU_SEEN_THE_DECORATIONS_THE_DOLL_FESTIVAL                         = 13494,  -- Have you seen the decorations? The Doll Festival has started, kupo!
        I_HEARD_FROM_MY_MOOGLE_SOURCES_THAT_THIS                                = 13495,  -- I heard from my moogle sources that this is a celebration for the health and happiness of girls, kupo.
        APPARENTLY_THE_YOUNG_LADY_AND_HER_BEAU_WOULD                            = 13496,  -- Apparently, the young lady and her beau would play empress and emperor, and would be joined by eight of their friends for the festivities, kupo.
        WHY_DON_T_YOU_TRY_MAKING_A_TEN                                          = 13497,  -- Why don't you try making a ten-person party as well? We can all have fun celebrating the Doll Festival, kupo!
        IT_LOOKS_LIKE_YOU_HAVE_ALL_THE_MEMBERS                                  = 13498,  -- It looks like you have all the members you need. Time for the festival to begin, kupo!
        AFTER_SQUEEZING_MY_MOOGLE_SOURCES_SOME_MORE_THEY                        = 13499,  -- After squeezing my moogle sources some more, they told me that people used to eat these during the festival. Here, you take one as well, kupo!
        IT_LOOKS_LIKE_YOU_HAVE_ALL_THE_MEMBERS_2                                = 13500,  -- It looks like you have all the members you need, kupo!
        IN_FACT_THE_MOOGLE_GRAPEVINE_TELLS_ME_THAT                              = 13501,  -- In fact, the moogle grapevine tells me that this is the perfect Doll Festival combination, kupo!
        AS_A_REWARD_FOR_YOUR_BLIND_LUC_I                                        = 13502,  -- As a reward for your blind luc--I mean, resourcefulness, I'm going to give you lots of these treats, kupo!
        JUST_IN_CASE_YOU_DIDN_T_KNOW_THE                                        = 13503,  -- Just in case you didn't know, the three girls in your party represent ladies of the court who wait on the empress. Moogles know everything about festivals, kupo!
        AND_BY_THE_WAY_THE_FIVE_GUYS_IN                                         = 13504,  -- And by the way, the five guys in your group represent musicians who entertain the empress and emperor. I wish I could play an instrument, kupo!
        KUPO_SOMETHING_S_NOT_RIGHT_AH_THIS_IS                                   = 13505,  -- Kupo!? Something's not right... Ah! This is a girl's festival and you don't have a girl in your party, kupo!
        KUPO_I_KNOW_I_SAID_THIS_WAS_A                                           = 13506,  -- Kupo... I know I said this was a girl's festival, but you need at least one guy to play the emperor, kupo.
        YOU_OBTAIN_AND                                                          = 13507,  -- You obtain % and %!
        YOU_OBTAIN_AND_2                                                        = 13508,  -- You obtain %, %, and %!
        YOU_OBTAIN_AND_3                                                        = 13509,  -- You obtain %, %, %, and %!
        YOU_OBTAIN_3_3_3_AND_3                                                  = 13510,  -- You obtain 3 %, 3 %, 3 %, and 3 %!
        KUPO_WHAT_HAPPENED_TO_YOUR_TEN_PERSON_PARTY                             = 13511,  -- Kupo? What happened to your ten-person party? You can't trick presents out of me, kupo!
        OOH_A_SHINY_NEW_ADVENTURER_JOIN_IN_THE                                  = 13512,  -- Ooh, a shiny new adventurer! Join in the fun, kupo!
        YOU_CAN_ONLY_CELEBRATE_THE_DOLL_FESTIVAL_ONCE                           = 13513,  -- You can only celebrate the Doll Festival once a day. Try again tomorrow, kupo!
        HEY_YOUR_PARTY_HAS_DIFFERENT_MEMBERS_ALL_OF                             = 13514,  -- Hey! Your party has different members all of a sudden! Well, I guess I can give you this for having the right number of people at least, kupo!
        HEY_YOUR_PARTY_HAS_LOST_TOUCH_WITH_ITS                                  = 13515,  -- Hey! Your party has lost touch with its feminine side! You need to find yourself a lady, kupo!
        HMM_YOU_SEEM_TO_HAVE_LOST_YOUR_MALE                                     = 13516,  -- Hmm... You seem to have lost your male element. Can't have the guys running away from you, kupo!
        WHAT_IS_THIS_CAN_T_YOU_SEE_THAT                                         = 13517,  -- What is this? Can't you see that I'm busy? ... Albanus? Bells? Alloys?
        EH_THAT_HAG_REINBERTA_TOLD_YOU_I_COULD                                  = 13518,  -- Eh? That hag Reinberta told you I could help? Here, let me see that scroll...
        HMPH_ALL_THIS_FANCY_JADE_REINBERTA_WOULD_LIKE                           = 13519,  -- Hmph. All this fancy jade... Reinberta would like something as useless as this. A good old iron clasp, now that's all you need. Sturdy, inexpensive, and practical, let me tell you...
        AHEM_NOW_WHAT_DOES_THIS_ALBANUS_CHARACTER_HAVE                          = 13520,  -- Ahem... Now, what does this Albanus character have to say...?
        HM_HRM_SO_THAT_IS_WHAT_HE_MEANS                                         = 13521,  -- Hm... Hrm... So that is what he means...
        IT_SEEMS_THAT_THE_ALLOY_OUR_BELLMAKER_IS                                = 13522,  -- It seems that the alloy our bellmaker is speaking of in his diary and on this scroll is Minstrel Metal.
        WHAT_YOU_VE_NEVER_HEARD_OF_IT_WELL                                      = 13523,  -- What? You've never heard of it? Well, of course you haven't. The method for making it has been lost for decades.
        MINSTREL_METAL_RECEIVES_ITS_NAME_FROM_THE_ENCHANTING                    = 13524,  -- Minstrel Metal receives its name from the enchanting sound that it emits when struck.
        THE_TONES_ARE_SO_BEAUTIFUL_THAT_IT_WAS                                  = 13525,  -- The tones are so beautiful, that it was said people would come from around the Kingdom just to hear the ballads created during the alloy's forging.
        I_BELIEVE_THAT_THIS_SCROLL_ILLUSTRATES_THE_LOST                         = 13526,  -- I believe that this scroll illustrates the lost method of smelting Minstrel Metal...but it is all written in some strange code. I can only guess the author did not want anyone to steal his techniques.
        BUT_IF_THAT_AUTHOR_REALLY_WAS_ALBANUS_THEN                              = 13527,  -- But if that author really was Albanus, then the cryptic message would make some sense.
        YOU_SEE_I_HAVE_HEARD_TALES_OF_THE                                       = 13528,  -- You see, I have heard tales of the eccentric young bellmaker...
        ONCE_LONG_AGO_THERE_WAS_A_NOVICE_GOLDSMITH                              = 13529,  -- Once, long ago, there was a novice goldsmith named Albanus who spent day and night studying the art of bellmaking. He was quite a prodigy, people said.
        MOST_OF_THE_TIME_THE_YOUNG_MAN_WOULD                                    = 13530,  -- Most of the time, the young man would lock himself up in his room behind the guild and pound away at his Minstrel Metal, until one day a strange boy called upon Albanus.
        THE_BOY_SAID_HE_HAD_BEEN_DRAWN_TO                                       = 13531,  -- The boy said he had been drawn to the voices of the angels, and asked if he could stay with Albanus.
        AT_FIRST_THE_BELLMAKER_WAS_PUZZLED_BUT_SOON                             = 13532,  -- At first the bellmaker was puzzled, but soon grew fond of the boy and his appreciation of Albanus's work. And though he himself was still an amateur, he allowed the boy to become his pupil, and proceeded to teach him the ways of smithing.
        HOWEVER_IT_TURNED_OUT_THAT_THE_PUPIL_DID                                = 13533,  -- However, it turned out that the pupil did more teaching than the master. The boy began telling Albanus how he was to create his bells, and it was not long before the boy's influence was heard in the song that rang forth from the novice goldsmith's workshop.
        BUT_THEN_ONE_DAY_THE_SOUND_STOPPED_JUST                                 = 13534,  -- But then one day, the sound stopped. Just as suddenly as the strange boy had appeared, he had vanished, and along with him, young Albanus...
        SOME_SAY_THAT_THE_ZEALOUS_BELLMAKER_SIMPLY_LEFT                         = 13535,  -- Some say that the zealous bellmaker simply left on a journey to discover new materials and techniques...
        WHILE_OTHERS_SAY_IT_WAS_THE_BOY_THAT                                    = 13536,  -- ...While others say it was the boy that forced Albanus to leave...
        THEY_SAY_THAT_HE_HAD_FOUND_A_WAY                                        = 13537,  -- They say that he had found a way inside Albanus's mind and made him go mad...
        BUT_IF_YOU_ASK_ME_I_DON_T                                               = 13538,  -- But if you ask me, I don't think it was either. You see, the job of an artist is to move the hearts of the masses.
        HOWEVER_WHEN_AN_ARTIST_BECOMES_TOO_ATTACHED_TO                          = 13539,  -- However, when an artist becomes too attached to his own work, strange things can begin to occur.
        EH_YOU_STILL_DON_T_UNDERSTAND_WHAT_I                                    = 13540,  -- Eh? You still don't understand what I'm trying to say?
        HAVEN_T_YOU_BEEN_LISTENING_AT_ALL                                       = 13541,  -- Haven't you been listening at all!?
        WHEN_AN_ARTIST_SPENDS_HIS_WHOLE_LIFE_WORKING                            = 13542,  -- When an artist spends his whole life working on something, a part of his soul is sometimes transferred to the piece.
        I_CANNOT_FULLY_EXPLAIN_THE_EXISTENCE_OF_THESE                           = 13543,  -- I cannot fully explain the existence of these newborn spirits, but there are many who believe in them.
        HOWEVER_ONE_THING_I_CAN_BE_CERTAIN_OF                                   = 13544,  -- However, one thing I can be certain of is this--if the boy who led poor Albanus away was truly born from a raw form of the bellmaker's passion, then he may be quite dangerous...
        KUPOPOPO_THIS_IS_TERRIBLE_VICIOUS_VILLAINS_ARE_VENTING                  = 13545,  -- Kupopopo`! This is terrible! Vicious villains are venting violently outside the city walls, kupo!
        WE_VE_DIVINED_THAT_THESE_CREATURES_ARE_INVULNERABLE                     = 13546,  -- We've divined that these creatures are invulnerable to normal weapons! And as if that wasn't enough, they're surrounded by a powerful aura that prevents them from being attacked at all, kupo!
        BUT_NEVER_FEAR_OUR_TOP_MOOGLE_RESEARCHERS_HAVE                          = 13547,  -- But never fear! Our top moogle researchers have created a weapon that can injure these invaders! Behold the wondrous %, kupo!
        THE_NOMAD_MOOGLES_HAVE_ALSO_DEVELOPED_A_MAGIC                           = 13548,  -- The nomad moogles have also developed a magic that will annul that anti-attack aura, so be sure to pay them a visit before you engage the enemy, kupo.
        BUT_BE_WARNED_THIS_MAGIC_HAS_THE_SIDE_2                                 = 13549,  -- But be warned--this magic has the side-effect of preventing you from attacking any other monster for three whole days, kupo!
        HERE_S_YOUR_NOW_YOU_RE_READY_TO                                         = 13550,  -- Here's your %. Now you're ready to do battle, kupo!
        THE_WILL_ABSORB_A_PART_OF_THE_VILLAIN                                   = 13551,  -- The % will absorb a part of the villain's aura every time you attack, kupo.
        EVEN_IF_YOU_DON_T_TOPPLE_THE_TERROR                                     = 13552,  -- Even if you don't topple the terror, bring the weapon to a moogle and you'll get a reward to match the amount of aura you've absorbed, kupo!
        BY_THE_WAY_THESE_MONSTERS_ARE_RUNNING_AROUND                            = 13553,  -- By the way, these monsters are running around in samurai-style armor. They may be hiding among other adventurers, so be on your guard, kupo!
        HERE_S_A_NEW_BRING_IT_BACK_TO                                           = 13554,  -- Here's a new %. Bring it back to a moogle if you deal any damage to those samurai-styled scoundrels, kupo!
        IF_YOU_WANT_TO_CROSS_SWORDS_WITH_THE                                    = 13555,  -- If you want to cross swords with the invincible interlopers, equip the % and talk to a nomad moogle, kupo!
        BRING_THE_WEAPON_TO_A_MOOGLE_AFTER_YOU                                  = 13556,  -- Bring the weapon to a moogle after you've inflicted some damage to the marauding monsters and you'll get a reward to match the amount of aura you've absorbed, kupo!
        I_CAN_SEE_THE_AURA_YOU_VE_ABSORBED                                      = 13557,  -- I can see the aura you've absorbed from the enemy! Here's your reward, kupo!
        WITH_ALL_THE_AURA_YOU_VE_ABSORBED_WITH                                  = 13558,  -- With all the aura you've absorbed with the %, we've managed to create a new weapon. We'd like you to have it, kupo!
        HAVE_YOU_EVER_HEARD_OF_BLITZ_BUFFALO_KUPO                               = 13559,  -- Have you ever heard of Blitz Buffalo, kupo? It's a fast and frenzied buffalo-chasing fiasco ferried in from a land to the far west of Quon!
        WE_MOOGLES_THOUGHT_IT_SOUNDED_LIKE_FUN_SO                               = 13560,  -- We moogles thought it sounded like fun! So we rounded up a bunch of buffalos and set them loose in several places, kupo!
        ALSO_WE_VE_TIED_AN_ITEM_TO_EACH                                         = 13561,  -- Also, we've tied an item to each buffalo! Anyone who catches one can keep the item as a reward! It's a great opportunity for adventurers, kupo!
        BUT_THE_BUFFALOS_AREN_T_GOING_TO_TAKE                                   = 13562,  -- But the buffalos aren't going to take a bunch of frantic adventurers chasing them lightly! You may have to knock one out before it yields its precious item, kupo!
        IF_YOU_MANAGE_TO_LAY_YOUR_HANDS_ON                                      = 13563,  -- If you manage to lay your hands on a buffalo, you better prepare to be flung around, kupo... Kupohoho`.
        OF_COURSE_IT_WOULDN_T_BE_TOO_GOOD                                       = 13564,  -- Of course, it wouldn't be too good if you ended up being the one chased either, kupo! Just take care, and good luck, kupo!
        IT_S_TIME_ONCE_AGAIN_FOR_THE_STARLIGHT                                  = 13565,  -- It's time once again for the Starlight Celebration!
        WE_MOOGLES_HAVE_COLLECTED_PILES_AND_PILES_OF                            = 13566,  -- We moogles have collected piles and piles of presents for the adventurers this time, kupo!
        WE_D_LIKE_TO_GIVE_THEM_TO_EACH                                          = 13567,  -- We'd like to give them to each person individually, but everyone always seems to be off on some adventure or another, and we can't keep them all straight! Could you help us, kupo?
        GIVE_THIS_CARD_TO_AN_ADVENTURER_AND_TELL                                = 13568,  -- Give this card to an adventurer and tell him or her to bring it to a moogle. We'll have a present waiting, kupo!
        THERE_ARE_FOUR_CARDS_IN_ALL_ONCE_YOU                                    = 13569,  -- There are four cards in all. Once you hand the first card out, I will ask the adventurer who brings it back to help with the next.
        YOU_LL_HELP_US_OUT_KUPO                                                 = 13570,  -- You'll help us out, kupo?
        HELP_THE_MOOGLES_I_LL_GIVE_IT_A                                         = 13571,  -- Help the moogles? I'll give it a try. I have other things to do.
        OH_I_JUST_REMEMBERED_I_THINK_THAT_THE                                   = 13572,  -- Oh, I just remembered! I think that the cards are all addressed to people who are wearing red...
        GOOD_LUCK                                                               = 13573,  -- Good luck!
        IF_YOU_CHANGE_YOUR_MIND_JUST_LET_ME                                     = 13574,  -- If you change your mind, just let me know, kupo.
        THIS_CARD_IS_ADDRESSED_TO_A_WITH_A                                      = 13575,  -- This card is addressed to a [warrior/monk/white mage/black mage/red mage/thief/paladin/dark knight/beastmaster/bard/ranger/samurai/ninja/dragoon/summoner] with a level range in the #s, kupo!
        THIS_CARD_IS_ADDRESSED_TO_A_WITH_A_2                                    = 13576,  -- This card is addressed to a [warrior/monk/white mage/black mage/red mage/thief/paladin/dark knight/beastmaster/bard/ranger/samurai/ninja/dragoon/summoner] with a level range in the #s, kupo!
        I_VE_BEEN_WAITING_I_VE_GOT_A                                            = 13577,  -- I've been waiting! I've got a present for you, kupo!
        I_HAVE_A_REQUEST_TOO_I_VE_GOT                                           = 13578,  -- I have a request, too. I've got presents for all the other adventurers, too, but I can't find everyone. I need your help, kupo!
        I_NEED_YOU_TO_GIVE_THIS_CARD_TO                                         = 13579,  -- I need you to give this card to a [warrior/monk/white mage/black mage/red mage/thief/paladin/dark knight/beastmaster/bard/ranger/samurai/ninja/dragoon/summoner] with a level range in the #s, and have them bring it back to me, kupo!
        OH_AND_THE_PERSON_SHOULD_BE_WEARING_THE                                 = 13580,  -- Oh, and the person should be wearing the same red clothing you are!
        I_LL_WAIT_HERE_AND_GET_THE_PRESENT                                      = 13581,  -- I'll wait here and get the present ready! Thanks, kupo!
        DID_YOU_HAND_OUT_THE_YET_KUPO_IF                                        = 13582,  -- Did you hand out the % yet, kupo? If you forgot who to give it to, just bring it to a moogle and you'll get a reminder.
        YOU_FORGOT_WHO_TO_GIVE_THE_TO_FIND                                      = 13583,  -- You forgot who to give the % to? Find a [warrior/monk/white mage/black mage/red mage/thief/paladin/dark knight/beastmaster/bard/ranger/samurai/ninja/dragoon/summoner] with a level range in the #s and hand it over, kupo!
        YOU_CAN_ONLY_HAND_OUT_ONE_CARD_A                                        = 13584,  -- You can only hand out one card a day, kupo!
        LET_ME_TELL_YOU_THE_KEY_TO_MAKING                                       = 13585,  -- Let me tell you the key to making the children of Vana'diel happy.
        YOU_HAVE_TO_GIVE_THEM_PRESENTS_THAT_MUCH                                = 13586,  -- You have to give them presents! That much should be obvious. I won't tell you what to give them, though. You've got to use your head for that!
        OH_YEAH_BEFORE_YOU_START_HANDING_OUT_GIFTS                              = 13587,  -- Oh yeah, before you start handing out gifts, you also have to wear one of these red hats like the one I've got on. That'll prove that you're a smilebringer! No kid will trust you without it!
        A_WHILE_AGO_I_SAW_A_MOOGLE_CARRYING                                     = 13588,  -- A while ago, I saw a moogle carrying a huge bag full of hats like this... Maybe they're selling them somewhere. You should find out for yourself! That's all I have to say!
        ID_13589                                                                = 13589,  -- [You haven't brought any happiness to the children!/You've done some good./You've done fairly well./You've made the children very happy!/You've brought lots of smiles!/You have the children bursting with glee!/The children love you!] [What a disappointment./You just need to give a little extra effort!/Keep it up!/You make a good smilebringer./Excellent work!/Stupendous job!/Even I think you're great!]
        YOU_CAN_MAKE_GOOD_USE_OF_SOME_OF                                        = 13590,  -- You can make good use of some of that joy you've brought to transport yourself to another nation. The children in other parts of Vana'diel need smiles, too!
        TRANSPORT_TO_ANOTHER_NATION_NOT_NOW_GO_TO                               = 13591,  -- Transport to another nation? Not now. Go to San d'Oria. Go to Bastok. Go to Windurst.
        HAVE_A_NICE_TRIP                                                        = 13592,  -- Have a nice trip!
        SORRY_BUT_IT_LOOKS_LIKE_YOU_DON_T                                       = 13593,  -- Sorry, but it looks like you don't have enough joy and happiness in your life to do that. You can earn some by giving presents to children, though!
        CALL_FOR_YES_NOT_NOW                                                    = 13594,  -- Call for [Feliz/Ferdinand/Gunnar/Massimo/Oldrich/Siegward/Theobald/Zenji]? Yes. Not now.
        CALL_FOR_YES_NOT_NOW_2                                                  = 13595,  -- Call for [Amerita/Beatrice/Henrietta/Jesimae/Karyn/Nanako/Sharlene/Sieghilde]? Yes. Not now.
        CALL_FOR_YES_NOT_NOW_3                                                  = 13596,  -- Call for [Chanandit/Deulmaeux/Demresinaux/Ephealgaux/Gauldeval/Grauffemart/Migaifongut/Romidiant]? Yes. Not now.
        CALL_FOR_YES_NOT_NOW_4                                                  = 13597,  -- Call for [Armittie/Cadepure/Clearite/Epilleve/Liabelle/Nauthima/Radille/Vimechue]? Yes. Not now.
        CALL_FOR_YES_NOT_NOW_5                                                  = 13598,  -- Call for [Balu-Falu/Burg-Ladarg/Ehgo-Ryuhgo/Kolui-Pelui/Nokum-Akkum/Savul-Kivul/Vinja-Kanja/Yarga-Umiga]? Yes. Not now.
        CALL_FOR_YES_NOT_NOW_6                                                  = 13599,  -- Call for [Cupapa/Jajuju/Kalokoko/Mahoyaya/Pakurara/Ripokeke/Yawawa/Yufafa]? Yes. Not now.
        CALL_FOR_YES_NOT_NOW_7                                                  = 13600,  -- Call for [Fhig Lahrv/Khuma Tagyawhan/Pimy Kettihl/Raka Maimhov/Sahyu Banjyao/Sufhi Uchnouma/Tsuim Nhomango/Yoli Kohlpaka]? Yes. Not now.
